(13, 1, '2011-09-16 17:58:58', '2011-09-16 17:58:58', 'With a huge participation as evident by the enthusiastic students at the various interactions during seminars, workshops and classes, Avishkar 2011 is surely going to mark its presence. Prizes worth lakhs have been declared and quite a good number of sponsors have already associated themselves with the fest. The team is getting very good response from colleges across the country regarding participation in the fest. Preparation is on full swing and as everyone can witness, the magic of AVISHKAR is slowly taking the pace.\r\nOnline registration started around 15 days back and more than 2000 outside participants have already registered for various events. Workshop on Robotics by iSENSOBOTZ Elex is scheduled for 2 days, 8hours everyday on 17th and 18th September at MNNIT Allahabad. Similarly another workshop on Ethical Hacking by Techdefence will be organized for 2 days each day 8 hour on 23rd and 24th September at MNNIT Allahabad. Interested students can register online or on the spot at the registration desk.\r\n\r\nAnd the list is not yet done. Get ready to witness the grand celebration of human intellectuality and dexterity.\r\nSo it’s time to break your inhibitions, unleash the passion within and let the technology and technical leadership flow within you.\r\nThe rivalry is around and so is the magic...', 'Avishkar---the magic is around.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'avishkar-the-magic-is-around', '', '', '2011-09-16 18:04:23', '2011-09-16 18:04:23', '', 0, 'http://172.31.100.16/blog/?p=13', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(15, 2, '2011-09-15 18:29:42', '2011-09-15 18:29:42', 'Every time, every day, we wish our lives were much simpler, happier…. And most of the time, we do nothing to change anything around us. Maybe it is the basic human nature to accept things the way they are even if things can be made better. We always want someone else to make it right for us or at least wish to. Because we know that it takes a lot of courage to reinvent ourselves.\r\nIt always seems that life is much simpler when we are young. But life is still simple. It is us who make our lives complicated. When we were young, we saw the world through simple, hopeful eyes. We knew what we wanted and we had no biases or concealed agendas. We liked people who smiled. We avoided people who frowned. We ate when we were hungry, drank when we were thirsty, and slept when we were tired. But now, as we have grown older, our minds have become gradually disillusioned by negative external influences. We hesitate and question our instincts.\r\nA new obstacle arises and we stumble and fall down several times. And eventually, we decide that we don’t want to fall again. And rather than solving the problem that made us fall, we avoid it all together. And this way, we suck life out of our lives, just because we are scared that we might fail, or be embarrassed or unsuccessful.\r\nWe eat junk and drink ‘Junker’ and stay up late at night just because we don’t want to face ourselves. We hold grudges, play mind games, and subtly deceive others and ourselves.\r\nOver the course of time, we have made our lives more and more difficult, and we have lost touch with those who we really are and what we really need.\r\nWe need to understand that life is not really a puzzle or a paradox or a question. It simply is LIFE!! And we need to reboot it….', 'Life Reboot', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'life-reboot', '', '', '2011-09-15 18:29:42', '2011-09-15 18:29:42', '', 0, 'http://172.31.100.16/blog/?p=15', 0, 'post', '', 0),
