(42, 4, '2011-09-23 09:27:30', '2011-09-23 09:27:30', 'If I ask you to list ten things that changed the human life, you’d probably say, fire, tools, clothes, animal domestication and so on. If I asked you to list ten things that changed human life in the last twenty years, you’d say: colour TVs, LCD projectors, EEGs, mobile phones, IPad and so on. We are, no doubt, part of a technology revolution and we’re lucky to be engineers.\r\n\r\nYes, you are an engineer and if someone calls you lazy, impatient or paranoid, you should be proud. Because the first automobile rolled out because the engineer was too lazy to walk. Because the e-mail was created because the engineer was impatient. Because in 1969, a manned mission was sent to the moon because engineers were paranoid. Yes, you can contribute to the world no matter how many excuses you give, just because YOU are engineers. I don’t care if you go home or stay back in the hostel watching sit-coms during the three days we call Avishkar, but make sure that you don’t miss the bandwagon leading straight into the technology revolution we’re headed to.\r\nWhat if you miss the train? Surely, nobody’s stopping your degree. Nobody can debar you from placements. With a good pointer, you’ll land up in a good company with a handsome package (i.e. if that is all you care about). But if you are part of Avishkar, you’d ALSO learn something that adds value to what you do, you’d ALSO have confidence when your boss tells you next time that this needs to be done, you’d ALSO have something to remember years down the line when you reflect on those wild night-outs in college making a robot walk or debugging a code, not for grades, but for yourself. And you’d have worked with a team with which you’ve had the best times in college.\r\nWe live in a democratic set-up. You have the freedom to choose. Make the right choice.\r\nI’m an alumnus who is proud to have learned a lot, in the last four years, from the three days of Avishkar and the long days and night-outs of preparation before that.\r\n\r\n--Mitesh Karwa\r\n\r\n( Mr. Mitesh Karwa is an Electrical engineer who graduated from MNNIT in the year 2011 and is currently working with Tata Motors Ltd.)', 'Reminiscences : a note from the alumni', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'reminiscences-a-note-from-the-alumni', '', '', '2011-09-23 09:27:30', '2011-09-23 09:27:30', '', 0, 'http://172.31.100.16/blog/?p=42', 0, 'post', '', 0),
