('electromania', 'Electromania', 'electromania', 'events', '<h4 align="center">Electronic circuits might have taken a long time to be invented but they certainly did not take a long time to make their presence felt in all walks of life. From small toys to state-of-the-art satellites, everything depends on electronic circuits.</h4><br/><br/><br/><p align="justify">\r\n\r\n\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/electromania.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="Electromania"></img>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>"The humble electron has come a long way from its lowly paths through a cathode ray tube. It has since been subjected to intense scrutiny by some of the most able and dauntless minds of the world, researchers dying to unravel the secrets it buries deep within its wave-particle duality. Meanwhile, technology enthusiasts have, over the decades, put it to myriad uses in applications ranging from simple amplifier circuits to interplanetary motion.<br><br>\r\n\r\nHere, at Avishkar 2011, we celebrate the electron in all its glory by holding ten contests that seek to explore all faces of the multi-faceted electron. We have something for everybody: PreDef, Embedded and OpenD for the hardcore Trical/Tronix guys, Penta, Sparks and War of the Currents for the more academic of us, and Impromptu, Connections and LiveWire for those who strike a middle ground between the two ends of the academic spectrum.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\nGet ready to breathe life into silicon, iron and copper."</b>\r\n<br><br> </p><br><br>\r\n<p align="center">Grand Prize for best overall performer in Avishkar among first year male and female MNNIT students: <b>BSA Cycle</b><br><br><br />\r\n  <img src="./sponsor/aricent.jpg" align="middle" /></center><br />Aricent Group</p>', 1),
('rasayans', 'Rasayans', 'rasayans', 'events', '<h4 align="center">I  consider nature a vast chemical laboratory in which all kinds of composition  and decompositions are formed. Vegetation is the basic instrument the creator  uses to set all of nature in motion.&rdquo;- Antoine  Lavoisier </h4> <br/><br/><br/> <p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/rasayans.jpg" width="40%" align="left" alt="rasayans"></img> 	Rasayans is the event to rear the nascent  initiatives for spread of chemical engineering education and foster the  interest of the budding engineers to become future stalwarts. <br />        A chemical engineer draws  upon the vast and powerfulscience of chemistry to solve a wide range of  problems. The strong technical and social ties that bind chemistry and  chemical engineering are unique in the fields of science and technology and Rasayans  provides the exotic podium to convert raw talent into technocrats of tomorrow.<br><br><br><br><br></p><br/><br/><p align="center">Grand Prize for best overall performer in Avishkar among first year male and female MNNIT students: <b>BSA Cycle</b><br><br></p>', 1),
('edifice', 'Edifice', 'edifice', 'events', '<h4 align="center" >Civil Engineering is the art of directing  the great sources of Power in Nature for the use and convenience of man,  where Imagination is  necessary as well as scientific knowledge. With our imagination  and knowledge we create a world for the growth of mankind. </h4><br/><br/><br/>  <p align="justify" > <img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/edifice.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="edifice"></img>  Edifice  is the civil engineering event which will judge your vision and technical  approach towards the problem, for the betterment of Human Social Need. Engineering problems are under-defined, there are many solutions, good,  bad and indifferent. The art is to arrive at a good solution. This is a  creative activity, involving imagination, intuition and deliberate choice. &nbsp;A good engineer is a person who makes a design that  works with as few original ideas as possible.<br><br></p> <br><br>\r\n<p align="center">Grand Prize for best overall performer in Avishkar among first year male and female MNNIT students: <b>BSA Cycle</b><br><br>Email: edifice.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</p>', 1),
