('genesis', 'Genesis', 'genesis', 'events', '<h4 align="center">"Great oaks from little acorns grow"</h4> <br><br><br> <p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:10px" src="events/genesis.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="genesis"></img> Bringing forth <b>Genesis.....</b><br><br> the biotechnological side of Avishkar with the quizzical tinge of <b>Double helix</b>, <br><br> the thrill of unravelling clues to unlock levels in <b>Cryptochrome</b>, <br><br> the chance to give a lecture of your own rather than being lectured, to present and be presented with new ideas in <b>Clairvoyance</b>....<br><br> <b>Bio-vision</b> for the culmination of the brightest and most ingenious minds and to unleash the creativity of budding biotechnologists....<br><br> the mind boggling <b>Paladin</b> and last but not the least <br><br> <b>Adrenaline Rush</b>, that, believe me, would surely excite your adrenal glands....<br><br>    <b>Genesis</b> promises to excite those neurons.... like never before...!!<br><br> There''s so much in store for those who dare to bash open the door. So what are you waiting for, this is everyone''s chance to Think, Create, Indulge and Discover...!! <br><br> The very sound of this might seem cliched, but the very experience will be of a carnival in short, and that''s a promise...!!<br><br>  So just take the plunge.....<br><br>  </p> <br/><br/><p align="center">Grand Prize for best overall performer in Avishkar among first year male and female MNNIT students: <b>BSA Cycle</b><br><br></p>', 1),
('robomania', 'Robomania', 'robomania', 'events', '<br><br><p align="justify"> <img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/robomania.png" width="30%"  align="left" alt="robomania"></img> <br /><br/>From the age of gladiators, we have gradually moved on to the era of transformers. The world has mechanised so swiftly that the odd feeling of change is virtually undetectable. Man has found his own way of playing God by producing the ultimate creation of all time - a robot.<br /><br/>  If you have a penchant for creating the incipient models of the robotic race which may one day inherit Earth, Robomania is the place where you can prove your indefeasible dominance. New robotic challenges await you<br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/></p><br/><br/> <p align="center">Grand Prize for best overall performer in Avishkar among first year male and female MNNIT students: <b>BSA Cycle</b><br><br></p>', 1),
('monopoly', 'Monopoly', 'monopoly', 'events', '<br><h4><center>The difference between a successful person and others is not a lack of strength, not a lack of knowledge, but rather a lack in will.</center></h4><br><br><p align="justify">\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:10px" src="events/monopoly.gif" width="50%" align="left" alt="image is loading"></img>\r\n\r\n\r\nThink you can be the next Steve Jobs? Or u can better Kishore Biyani with your own innovative ideas?\r\nSo step in, the only "non-technical" series of events in Avishkar 2011 called the MONOPOLY. \r\nIt is aimed at getting the participants to test their leadership, marketing, advertising, decision making and entrepreneurial abilities. MONOPOLY would be surely a lot of fun & you will be able to explore your innovative ideas.\r\nKnowing is not enough; we must apply.\r\nWilling is not enough; we must do.<br/><br/><br/></p><br/><br/><p align="center">Grand Prize for best overall performer in Avishkar among first year male and female MNNIT students: <b>BSA Cycle</b><br><br></p>\r\n', 1),
('jigyasa', 'Jigyasa', 'jigyasa', 'events', '<h1><center><u>School Bag Event</u></center></h1>\r\n<br /><br /><h4><center>"Millions saw apples fall, but only Newton asked why"</center></h4>\r\n<br>\r\n<br /><p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:60px" src="events/jigyasa.png" width="50%" align="left" alt="image is loading"></img>\r\nEquipped with his five senses, man explores the universe around him and calls \r\nthe adventure Science. Here comes a rigorous scientific tournament which \r\ninvigorates in you the passion to innovate, the zeal to create and the lust to \r\nlearn. It is one of the most challenging and motivational events, well balanced \r\nbetween the various science disciplines of chemistry, physics, mathematics and \r\ntechnology. Gear yourself up for the upcoming expedition to explore the real \r\nscientist within you.</p>\r\n<br/><br/><p align="center">Prize for Best Student: <b>BSA Cycle</b><br />Best School will be awarded a <b>Trophy</b><br />\r\n<br />\r\nEmail: <strong>jigyasa.aviskar2k11@gmail.com</strong></p>', 1),
