INSERT INTO `tabs` (`id`, `tab_no`, `name`, `description`, `display`) VALUES
('insomnia', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4><i><center>"This isn''t magic - it''s logic - a puzzle."  Hermione - harry potter and the philosophers stone\r\n</center></i></h4><br /><br /><br/>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:60px" src="events/insomnia.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="insomnia"></img>How many times has it happened to you when you sacrificed your dinner for that last\r\npiece of optimisation that just showed up out of nowhere..or when you had a hangover\r\nafter coding six hours straight throughout the night. It''s the mid-historical warfare\r\nbetween the owls of programming, staying out nights scratching heads. Yes, its time\r\nfor geek Halloween. Are you ready ?<br/>\r\nThe crux of this event is your code,the algorithm that is agile enough to pass through\r\nthe time and memory limits - All within a span of 6 hours.<br/>\r\nEnjoy the lead while you can as there is always someone better, faster and tougher\r\nthan you are.\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('inception', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4><i><center>An opening wedge for the rookies.</center></i></h4><br /><br /><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/inception.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="inception"></img>Show  us the will, we will show you the way&quot;. The event being specifically  designed for the first year students does not require participants to be  acquainted with technical jargons and concepts, all that is required is  willingness to learn and good logical and reasoning abilities. It will be a  hands-on experience for the newbies on how the things happen in the arena where  they have just entered. So, all the first years, do remember-<br /><br />\r\n  &quot;<strong><em>Everyone  stands beneath a mountain,some just keep standing, some walk around, some take  the first step, the result being obvious</em></strong>&quot;<br /><br />\r\n  Hence,  gear up yourself, start this very moment, a bright future surely awaits.</p>', 'y'),
('inception', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ol type="1">\r\n<li>This event is open only to the B.Tech first year and MCA 1st year students irrespective of their branch.</li><br>\r\n<li>It is an individual event.</li><br>\r\n<li>Obscenity is highly discouraged and will leave to instant disqualification.</li><br>\r\n<li>The decision of the Event Coordinators will be final and binding.</li><br>\r\n\r\n</ol>', 'y'),
('softathalon', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4><i><center>The Big one before the Big One</center></i></h4><br /><br /><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:10px" src="events/softathalon.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="softathalon"></img>Softathalon is the most coveted and sought after event of CyberQuest and undoubtedly the most rewarding one where your knowledge and commitment shall be the only aid following the modus operandi "Every Man for Himself" . Softathalon is an event meant for finding out a complete software techie. This event will be checking your programming, logical analysis, aptitude and other technical skills. <br/><br/>\r\nCyberQuest @ Avishkar 2k11 marks the inception of a revamped Softathalon , more "Edgier", a bit "Peppier" and surely much more "Gruelling" version of the past iterations. \r\nSo put your software dexterity to the test and emerge as the ultimate software techie.\r\n<br><br>\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('softathalon', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br> <ol type="1"><li>This is an Individual Event.</li><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Anybody found breaking rules or violating instructions given, will be debarred from Cyberquest .</li><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Decision of coordinators will be final, no queries regarding rechecking will   be  entertained.</li><br>\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
('software_design', 1, 'Introduction', '\r\n<h4><i><center>Making the simple complicated is commonplace; making the complicated simple, awesomely simple, that''s creativity.</center></i></h4><br /><br /><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:10px" src="events/software_design.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="software_design"></img>Here is the golden opportunity to get to know how things are done. The games you have played, applications you used and much more. Time to come out of "USER MODE" and get yourself into implementing those things. You will also have the opportunity to know the language that is grabbing its hold upon the software world, "THE JAVA".<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br><br><br />The last date for the submission of Round 1 problem statements in Software Design for outside participants is 17th September 2011 by 12 midnight.<br /><br /></p>', 'y'),
('software_design', 4, 'Rules', '<br><br><ol type="1">\r\n        <li>Each team can comprise a maximum of three members.</li><br>\r\n<li>A student can be a member of only one team.</li><br>\r\n<li>One team can submit only one entry of each problem.</li><br>\r\n<li>There is no restriction on the participating students except that at least one must be from C.S.E/IT.</li><br>\r\n<li>Copied code from internet or any other source will lead to disqualification.</li><br>\r\n<li>Participants can make use of any platform (Linux or Windows) and any         \r\n         language of their choice (JAVA, .NET, even C/C++) but remember it must be a\r\n         software not a program, proper Graphical user interface should be there.</li><br>\r\n<li> Students will be shortlisted for the second round based on the marks of first       \r\n         round. Then final results will be based upon the aggregate marks of both Second\r\n         and Third round.    </li><br>\r\n                  <li>Remember quality of features is more important than the quantity.</li><br>\r\n    \r\n', 'y'),
('insomnia', 3, 'Rules', ' <br><br><ol type="1">\r\n <li>Disscusion of topics among the different teams at the time of event is strictly prohibited. However  group members of the same team can discuss among themselves.</li><br>\r\n<li>Final round will be a open book round. Students are allowed to bring printed or written material but any mass storage devices like pen drives are not allowed. </li><br>\r\n<li>Students cannot access internet either through computer or in any ways during the event. </li><br>\r\n<li>Decision of the  co-ordinators is final and co-ordinators have right to change any of the rule if required.</li><br>\r\n<li>Violation of any rule or any act of misconduct can lead to debarment from Cyberquest.</li><br></ol>\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
('debugging', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4><i><center>DEBUGGING\r\nDebugging is twice as hard as writing the code in the first place. Therefore, if you write the code as cleverly as possible, you are, by definition, not smart enough to debug it.\r\n</center></i></h4><br /><br /><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/debugging.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="debugging"></img>A completely refined and changed event from last year to challenge your debugging skills and knowledge about C/C++ program, no matter you have its source code or not. Where others stop at undefined-behaviors, this event start at defining them.<br/>\r\nIf you can tear apart the code to bits, reverse-engineer it in order to debug it, this is the right place for you. So reload gdb-47, sharpen your objdump-axe and start filling your arsenal for war with bugs, faults and errors.\r\n<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>\r\n\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('debugging', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ol type="1">\r\n<li>There should be a team of maximum two participants.</li><br>\r\n<li>Working environment: Plateform: Linux (32-bit), Compiler: g++/gcc</li><br><li>Participants can team up with students of any branch and any year except Final year.</li><br>\r\n<li>Only one computer will be provided to each team in final round.</li></ol><br><br>\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
('breakthrough', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4><i><center>Innovation distinguishes between a leader and a follower</center></i></h4><br /><br /><br/>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/breakthrough.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="breakthrough"></img>An innovation is one of those things that society looks at and says, if we make this part of the way we live and work, it will change the way we live and work. This is a search for the budding scientists spread across. Give life to the Einstein in you and build up those pieces of imaginations to make your world glow. Let your innovations be the religion of the future. So come forward with your ideas and provide a Breakthrough in the world of Computers.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br> <br><br><br></p><br><br>\r\n<p align="center">Download:<br><u><b><a href="events/breakthrough1.pdf" target="_blank">Example IEEE</a></b></u> || <u><b><a href="/events/breakthrough2.pdf" target="_blank">Sample IEEE format paper</a></b></u></p>', 'y'),
('breakthrough', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ol type="1">\r\n<li>A team can consist a maximum of three members.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>All abstracts have to be submitted via mail to <a href="mailto:breakthrough.avishkar2k11@gmail.com"><b>breakthrough.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</b></a>.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>Maximum word limit of abstract submission  is 100 words</li><br><br>\r\n<li>The deadline for the submission of the abstracts is 15 September 2011 by 12 midnight.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The final paper should be in the IEEE double column format, with a maximum of 6 pages.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Simulation, implementation, statistical analysis or results supporting the idea would carry \r\n  extra weightage.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The papers will be judged on the basis of originality, feasibility, coherence, and the\r\n  presentation skills.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Originality of the idea is a must. Copied papers and any kind of duplicity will lead to\r\n  disqualification.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Referring to previously published papers is permitted; however make sure you contribute\r\n  more to your paper than all the papers you are referring to.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Do not copy contents from the internet or elsewhere, if you can google so can we ;)<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Decision of the judges is final.<br><br></li></ol><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('mobile_mania', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4><i><center>The Future is... Mobile</center></i></h4><br /><br /><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:60px" src="events/mobile_mania.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="mobile_mania"></img>Today  in this fast world, size of every gadget is decreasing. Computers have now  transformed from large desktops to palmtops. The future ahead is of device programming.<br /><br/>\r\n  So, <strong>MobileMania</strong> is a window to the future. It''s all about developing mobile  applications. It is a new era of  technology and only few people are pro in this field. All related companies are  encouraging and investing a huge amount in this field like Google, Microsoft,  Apple, Samsung, etc. <br><br>The last date for the submission of Round 1 problem statements in Mobilemania is 15th September 2011 by 12 midnight.</p>', 'y'),
('mobile_mania', 4, 'Rules', '<br><br><ol type="1">\r\n<li>You can participate with a team of two or three members.</li><br>\r\n<li>A member can be a part of only one team.</li><br>\r\n<li>Copy and paste solutions will be rejected and strict actions will be taken agaisnt them.</li><br>\r\n<li>You can submit the code in Android or J2ME ONLY.</li><br>\r\n<li>Stick to the submission deadlines.</li><br>\r\n<li>For round 2: Sumit your solutions with a brief description of it in a README file. (See the FAQs for details on what to put in the README file).</li><br>\r\n</ol><br>', 'y'),
('code_warriors', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4><i><center>Keep up your bright swords, for the dew will rust them -  Othello, Shakespeare </center></i></h4><br /><br /><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/code_warriors.png" width="50%" align="left" alt="Code Warriors"></img>The best Othello computer programs have easily defeated the best humans since 1980, Logistello is a computer program that plays the game Othello which has beaten the human world champion Takeshi Murakami six games to none in 1997.<br/>\r\nNow its your chance to build a bot that is an epitome of excellence, that can break the logic of the most cogent of programs, and emerge out as invincible. So get ready to put your gray matter into action, for now its not you, its your bot that is going to compete for glory.<br><br>\r\n<br />\r\n\r\nFor Outside participants, who will not able to come onsite on the day of judgement during Avishkar, you can mail your code at <a href="mailto:codewarriors.avishkar2k11@gmail.com"><b>codewarriors.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</b> and your match can be conducted on your behalf. You will be mailed detail of the match (all the moves played during the match) for your satisfaction.\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><br><br>', 'y'),
('code_warriors', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ol type="1">\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Each team can have a maximum of 3 members.</li><br>\r\n<li>Event is fully automated. Your codes will run on a judge.</li><br>\r\n\r\n<li>There will be one on one matches. The winner will be decided on the basis of the moves that your code makes.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Your code must adhere to the rules of the game and the time restrictions.</li><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Languages allowed are : C/C++ (gcc/g++ compilers only).</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>The organizers reserve the right to change any rule of the game or the time restrictions. Any change will be updated and highlighted in the problem statement. All registered participants will be notified.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Judges decision will be final and binding on all.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li>For Outside participants, who will not able to come onsite on the day of judgement during Avishkar, you can mail your code at <a href="mailto:codewarriors.avishkar2k11@gmail.com"><b>codewarriors.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</b></a> and your match can be conducted on your behalf. You will be mailed detail of the match (all the moves played during the match) for your satisfaction.</li><br></ol>\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
('tuxwars', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4><i><center>The choice of the GNU generation.</center></i></h4><br /><br /><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/tuxwars.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="tuxwars"></img>The time of reckoning has come.... the gods are calling upon the mightiest warriors for the war of software giants. Will your faith in the open source be enough!!!!!!! We take you to a journey where open source is your only friend, no patent, no copyright. Here you fight for something more, here you fight for the greater good ..... the enlightenment of the coding world. Bask in the glory ...... that is yours if you survive this war. Suit up ..... for you are in a realm where you cannot rest until you dismantle the inner working of unix ..... a nightmare for all but the chosen few ..... the chosen warriors of tux wars!!!<br /><br /><br><br><br><br></p>', 'y'),
('tuxwars', 3, 'Rules', '<br /><br /><ol type="1">\r\n<li>The team may consist of at most 2 members. <br><br></li>\r\n<li>The teams must adhere to the spirit of HEALTHY COMPETITION.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Judges reserve the right to disqualify any team found indulging in misbehavior.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Judges decision shall be final and binding on all.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The organizers reserve the rights to change any or all of the above rules as they deem fit. Change in rules, if any will be highlighted on the website and notified to the registered participants.<br><br></li></ol>\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
('code_of_the_day', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4><i><center>Big &lsquo;O&rsquo; is all  that matters</center></i></h4><br /><br /><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:10px" src="events/code_of_the_day.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="Code_of_the Day"></img>Hello, Mr. Michael Scofield. Welcome to Fox River state penitentiary. It''s time to commence your mission to break out with your innocent brother. To accomplish this task you need to use your acumen and skills. From here onwards, every step of yours will decide whether you win or lose. Not only perfection but speed will decide your fate.So sync up the clock, lay down the plan and go over the prison walls. \r\n<br><br>The event Code of the Day will be launched on 11th September 2011 at 9 pm.<br><br></p>', 'y'),
('code_of_the_day', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ol start="1" type="1">\r\n  <li>This is an individual event. <br><br></li>\r\n  <li>One question will be uploaded every day at 9 p.m., the questions will be of       increasing difficulty. <br><br></li>\r\n  <li>Solutions are to be submitted by mail to <a href="mailto:codeoftheday.avishkar2k11@gmail.com"><b>codeoftheday.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</b></a> latest by 9 p.m. on the next day. <br><br>\r\n\r\n Subject of the mail should be the Title of the Problem of That Day.<br><br><ol type="a">\r\n  <li>Body of the mail should  contain your name, branch, year and college and Avishkar registration ID.<br><br></li>\r\n  <li> Source code file (.c/.cpp/.java) should be sent as an  attachment.<br><br></li>\r\n  <li>Compiler used will be gcc for C and g++ for C++. &nbsp;For java jdk version 1.6 will be used.<br><br></li></ol></li>\r\n<br>\r\n  <li>Rank will be according to fastest and correct submission.<br>\r\n  <br></li>\r\n \r\n  <li>Marking       scheme will be as follows-</li><br><br>\r\n</ol>\r\n<table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr height="20px">\r\n    <th width="160" valign="top">Rank</th>\r\n    <th width="160" valign="top">Level &ndash;A</th>\r\n    <th width="160" valign="top">Level-B</th>\r\n    <th width="160" valign="top">Level-C</th>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="20px">\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">1st</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">100</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">150</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">200</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="20px">\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">2nd</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">90</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">135</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">180</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="20px">\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">3rd</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">80</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">120</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">160</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="20px">\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">4th</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">70</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">105</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">140</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="20px">\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">5th</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">60</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">90</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">120</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="20px">\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">6th</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">50</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">75</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">100</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="20px">\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">7th</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">50</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">75</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">100</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="20px">\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">8th</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">50</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">75</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">100</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="20px">\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">9th</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">50</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">75</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">100</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="20px">\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">10th</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">50</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">75</td>\r\n    <td width="160" valign="top">100</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table><br><br>\r\n<ol start="6" type="1">\r\n<li>  Multiple submissions can be made, only the last submission will be considered. However, 10 \r\npoints will be deducted on every extra submission. Minimum score will be 10.<br><br></li>\r\n  <li>Results of each day&rsquo;s question will be       declared by midnight on the next day. <br><br></li>\r\n  <li>Overall       winner will be declared after completion of event. <br><br></li>\r\n  <li>Use       of any unfair means will be dealt with disqualification; judge&rsquo;s decision       will be final. <br><br></li>\r\n  <li>All       programs are to be written in C/C++/Java. But we would suggest to prefer       C/C++ as in case of codes submitted at the same time, java codes may run       slower than C/C++ codes. <br><br></li>\r\n</ol><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('webster', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4><i><center>Good design keeps the user happy, the manufacturer in the black and the aesthete unoffended.</center></i></h4><br /><br /><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/webster.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="webster"></img>It is not Spiderman''s web; it''s the World Wide Web!!! Since Tim Berners Lee, who published the first website in August 1991, the desire of transformation in cyberspace multiplied. Today, in the pool of cyberspace, everybody has a natural interest in witnessing change taking place before his/her eyes. Now is your chance to become a part of this cyber-pool. Design your own website on our guidelines. Are you the one to come up with the most stupendous design with a myriad of web functionalities..???\r\n<br><br><br>\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('webster', 4, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\nEach team can have a maximum of 3 members. <br><br>\r\n<ol><li>\r\nRegister your Team name, Team members and College Name at\r\n<a href="http://www.tinyurl.com/webster2011" target="_blank"><b>registration portal.</b></a> You can also contact us in case of queries.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>There is no limit for space/size of the website. <br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>You can use any platform of your choice.Example : PHP, JSP, .NET, Ruby on rails ,etc. <br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>You are allowed to use Content Management Systems like Joomla, Drupal,\r\nWordPressetc unless it is restricted  in the problem statement.You need to mention this in your abstract.<b>Extra marks will be awarded if you make your own template and use it.</b> <br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>Proper documentation is expected having descriptions of all the files, databases, server\r\nscripts, etc. <br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>In case you are using flash and/or self made images, the source files .fla/.psd/.png etc.\r\nare to be provided (with all layers present) in a separate folder and also you have to mention so in the abstract.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>The decision of the judges and co-ordinators will be final and binding on all the participants. <br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>Multiple problem statements will be uploaded . You can choose at most two of the statements for the abstract submission round.But, you have to submit the abstract for each problem seperately.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>There will be a separate problem for B.Tech. first year students of MNNIT and the team from first year can choose any problem of there choice, but the maximum submission allowed for the abstract round will still be two.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<b>Distribution of Marks:</b><br><br>\r\n<ol><li>Abstract-5%<br></li>\r\n<li>Design and Presentation-10%<br></li>\r\n<li>Database Design-20%<br></li>\r\n<li>Security features -25%<br></li>\r\n<li>Deployment-10%<br></li>\r\n<li>Fulfillment of Objectives-20%<br></li>\r\n<li>Extra Features-10%<br><br></li></ol>\r\n', 'y'),
('iopc', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4><i><center>The link is <br> <a href="http://www.codechef.com/IOPC11" target="_blank">http://www.codechef.com/IOPC11</a>\r\n</center></i></h4><br /><br /><br/>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/iopc.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="iopc"></img>IOPC is International Online Programming Contest Organised by MNNIT as a part of Avishkar. Its not just an event, it a fierce battle of wits between coders from all around the world. Time is limited, problems are hard, do you have in you what it takes to be the best. If yes then enjoy the lead while you can as there is always someone better, faster and tougher than you are.\r\n<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p><center>The timing for the Contest is 6:00PM on 22nd October, 2011<br></center><br><br>', 'y'),
('iopc', 3, 'Rules', '<br /><br /><ol type="1"><li> Team of maximum two is allowed. One person cant be part of more than one team.</li><br />\r\n\r\n    <li>Languages allowed: C/C++/Java.</li><br>\r\n\r\n    <li>Contest duration: 6 hours with 6 problems.</li><br>\r\n\r\n    <li>Each problem has its own time limit which will be given with the problem itself.</li><br>\r\n\r\n    <li>No system calls and No file I/O will be allowed.</li><br>\r\n\r\n    <li>gcc/g++/jdk1.3 (version 4.3.2 or higher ) will be used for compilation.</li><br />\r\n<br /><br /></ol>', 'y'),
('insomnia', 4, 'FAQS', '<br>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 1.</td><td>Who can participate?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Any student from any college or university in India or abroad can participate.\r\n\r\n </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 2.</td><td >What are the technical requirments for the final coding rounds?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Simple Data Structures and algorithms are atleast required.\r\n</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 3.</td><td >What is the size of each team?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Each team can have a maximum of 3 participants.\r\n\r\n</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 4.<br><br></td><td >Where can I get more information regarding the event?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:<br><br></td><td>Send any queries regarding the event to<a href="mailto:insomnia.avishkar2k11@gmail.com"><b> insomnia.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</b></a> with subject as"QUERY".\r\n\r\n</td></tr>\r\n</table><br/><br/>\r\n', 'y'),
('fpga', 3, 'Rules', '<br /><br /><b>RULES AND REGULATIONS:-</b><br /><br />\r\n<ol><li> There can be a maximum of 4 members in the same team. The members of the team need not be from the same institution. All members should be current students of a recognized educational institution. All teams and their members should register themselves failing which, their participation in the final rounds will not be considered.<br /><br />\r\n<li>The competition shall consist of two rounds. The first round, the preliminaries, will consist of the submission of an abstract that details the approach adopted by the team towards solving the problem and any progress made already. The abstract should clearly outline the following details:<br><br>\r\n<ul><li>Team details (members and their institutions, contact details including phone numbers and email addresses of each member and team name). <br><br></li>\r\n<li>Brief introduction to the problem statement (to test your understanding of what is required). <br><br></li>\r\n<li>Your approach towards solving the problem, including design decisions as well as technical details. <br><br></li>\r\n<li>Work already completed (in which case a snapshot of current code is required).<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Estimated time of completion.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Any other comments.<br><br></li></ul></li>\r\n<li>The final round of the competition will consist primarily of a presentation by the team, involving the following:<br><br>\r\n<ul><li>Design decisions and implementation details.<br><br></li><li>A test run on the reference software simulator and on the kit.<br><br></li><li>A viva round.<br><br></li><li>Any other specific request made by the judges.<br><br></li></ul></li>\r\n<li>Any kind of plagiary will lead to disqualification from ELECTROMANIA 2K11.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Mail your abstracts to <b><a href="mailto:fpga.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">fpga.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b><br><br> The deadline for abstract submission is 11:59pm, 10th Sept, 2011.<br><br></li></ul><br></li></ol>\r\n', 'y'),
('open_design', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br>\r\n<h4 align="center">"The world is a dangerous place, not because of those who do evil, \r\nbut because of those who look on and do nothing": Albert Einstein\r\n\r\n</h4><br><br><br>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/open_design.jpg" width="50%" align="left"  alt="open_design"></img>The event aims at testing the creativity of the participants. In Open Design you have to design an electronic/electrical/mechanical system that may have any practical application. You are not bound to choose a category but are totally free to explore through the long list of possibilities. This is a perfect platform for you to find the INVENTOR in you to produce your new AVISHKAR to the world. You can design a hardware circuit or a software simulation to participate in the event..<br><br>\r\nIn short this is <b>"THE REAL AVISHKAR"</b>.\r\n\r\n<br><br><br><br><br><br><br> </p><br><br><br>', 'y'),
('open_design', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Team of maximum three  members irrespective of branch and year.</li><br>\r\n  <li>Hardware containing  fabricated parts is not allowed (except for basic parts such as ICs, motors,  sensors etc.).<strong> </strong></li><br>\r\n  <li>Software simulation should be  on new innovative ideas. Existing samples would be disqualified if used.<strong> </strong></li><br>\r\n  <li>Final judging will be done  by faculty members of electrical department.</li><br>\r\n  <li>Hardware designs would be  given preference over software simulations.</li><br>\r\n  <li>More simplified solution to  a more complex problem is preferential to judges.</li><br>\r\n  <li>The description for the  elimination round has to be submitted latest by 11:59 PM on 19th  September 2011.</li><br>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'y'),
('pentathalon', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br>\r\n<h4 align="center">"Wisdom is like electricity. There is no permanently wise man, but men capable of wisdom, \r\nwho, being put into certain company, or other favorable conditions, become wise for a short time, \r\nas glasses rubbed acquire electric power for a while."-Ralph Waldo Emerson\r\n</h4><br><br><br>\r\n<p align="justify"><br><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" align="left" src="events/pentathalon.jpg" width="50%"  alt="pentathalon"></img><br/><br/>"A five round frenzy. A test- of awareness and knowledge of the known and of your nerves to face the unknown. A winner."<br><br>\r\nPut your technical prowess (electrical & electronics related) and analytic acumen to test,\r\nif you think you have what it takes to be called-unarguably the best."\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p><br><br>', 'y'),
('pentathalon', 4, 'Rules', '<br /><br /><ol type="1">\r\n<li>This would be an individual event.</li><br />\r\n\r\n<li>1st year-Open for all branches.<br /> \r\n     for 2nd & 3rd year-   Electronics & Electrical branches only.</li><br />\r\n\r\n<li> All rounds are elimination rounds.</li><br />\r\n\r\n<li>There would be separate papers & cut-offs for all three years.</li><br />\r\n\r\n<li> Decision of organizers would be final and binding.</li><br />\r\n\r\n<li> The students must be present with valid identity cards at the time of event.</li><br />\r\n<li> Any kind of plagiary will lead to disqualification from ELECTROMANIA 2K11.</li><br />\r\n\r\n<li> Participants from other colleges need to register yourself for the event at  <a href="mailto:pentathlon.avishkar2k11@gmail.com"><b>pentathlon.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</b></a> to confirm your participation in the event.</li><br /></ol><br /><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
('live_wire', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br>\r\n<h4 align="center">"Coding Live into the jaws of night"</h4><br><br><br>\r\n<p align="justify">	<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/live_wire.JPG" width="50%" align="left"  alt="live_wire"></img>If hours of programming gives you the vibes and appeals to your nerves, <br><br>\r\nthen come along and rack your brains in the ultimate battle, played on the fields of software. <br><br>\r\nSo let''s create a new regime of code while all the world rests in dreamless slumber. <br><br>\r\nLiveWire is a programming contest - the rules of the game are the C/++ language, PSpice, MATLAB and LabVIEW. <br><br>\r\nCome, pit your brains against MNNIT''s finest in an all-nighter epic showdown contest.<br><br></p><br><br><br><br> \r\n', 'y'),
('live_wire', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ol type="1"><li>Each team shall comprise a maximum of three participants. The participants need not necessarily be from the same institute provided their college administration allows them</li><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The contestants can be students pursuing undergraduate studies in any recognized University across the globe</li><br>\r\n<li>Students from different years may pool together to form a team. However, for evaluation purposes, the team shall be deemed at par with the team composed entirely of the same year as that of the senior most participant in such a team</li><br>\r\n\r\n<li>There is no restriction on the allowed branches. However, for evaluation, all branches shall be treated at par</li><br>\r\n<li>Only the teams that clear the preliminary round shall advance to the finals.</li><br>\r\n\r\n<li> Resorting to unfair means at any stage of the event is highly discouraged and will result in  instant disqualification from ELECTROMANIA 2K11</li><br>\r\n\r\n<li> Usage of internet, mobile phones, pagers or any other communicating device in the final round is prohibited and will result in disqualification</li><br>\r\n\r\n<li> The more efficient a code, the more likely it is to fetch points</li><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The coordinators'' evaluation will be final. No arguments in this regard will be entertained</li><br>\r\n\r\n<li> In the unlikely event of a dispute or disagreement, the coordinators'' word shall be final and binding</li><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The students must be present with valid identity cards at the time of event</li><br></ol>\r\n<br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('pre_defined_hardware', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br>\r\n<h4 align="center">Engineers are those that turn coffee into circuits\r\n</h4><br><br><br>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/predefined_hardware.jpg" width="50%" align="left"  alt="predefined"></img>\r\nEngineering is the supreme tool by which man causes inanimate objects to obey his will. In this event, you will be required to employ whatever theory the textbooks preach in the hardware-level solution of a problem. And in the process, experience all those elements that usually get filtered out in the equations thanks to approximations and assumptions. Predefined Hardware aims to make the budding engineer fully cognizant of the things to be kept in mind while porting an engineering solution from paper to the real world.\r\n\r\n\r\n<br></p><br><br><br><br> \r\n', 'y'),
('pre_defined_hardware', 5, 'Contacts', '<br><br>\r\n<b>Problem Statement 1</b><br><br>\r\n<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr height="30px">\r\n    <td width="300px">Avichal  Kulshrestha </td>\r\n    <td width="300px">+91-9410208476</td>\r\n    <td width="300px">avichalkul@gmail.com</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="30px">\r\n    <td width="300px">Tushar Rastogi </td>\r\n    <td width="300px">+91-9451433034</td>\r\n    <td width="300px">tusharrastogi007@gmail.com </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br><br><br>\r\n<b>Problem Statement 2</b><br><br>\r\n<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n  <tr height="30px">\r\n    <td width="300px">Avichal  Kulshrestha </td>\r\n    <td width="300px">+91-9410208476</td>\r\n    <td width="300px">avichalkul@gmail.com</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="30px">\r\n    <td width="300px">Gaurav Yadav </td>\r\n    <td width="300px">+91-9452629641</td>\r\n    <td width="300px">gauravyadav083@gmail.com </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n    <tr height="30px">\r\n    <td width="300px">Guru Das S.</td>\r\n    <td width="300px">+91-9452933184</td>\r\n    <td width="300px">gurooodas@gmail.com</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr height="30px">\r\n    <td width="300px">Nitesh Kumar Chaudhary</td>\r\n    <td width="300px">+91-9452935395</td>\r\n    <td width="300px">gnakshatra.om@gmail.com </td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br><br><br>\r\n \r\n \r\n<b>NOTE:</b>  Participants should register themselves by dropping in a mail to \r\n<b><a href="mailto:electromania.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">electromania.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b> giving following details: <br><br>\r\n<ol><li>Team name <br><br></li>\r\n<li>College name <br><br></li>\r\n<li>Name of members with year and branch. <br><br></li></ol>', 'y'),
('sparks', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br>\r\n<h4 align="center">"Somewhere, something incredible is waiting to be known." \r\n</h4><br><br><br>\r\n<p align="justify">	<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/sparks.jpg" width="50%" align="left"  alt="sparks"></img>\r\nThe uncontainable passion takes its roots from an earnest desire to explore new horizons and to discover our own unique potential. One fine day the melting pot of dreams and passions..seethes over and suddenly igniting everything in its path and turning us all who are close to it instruments for achieving this collective dream. This becomes the passion that surrounds us all and right there in the midst of the multitude, it then becomes a vision, a goal, our goal.<br><br>\r\nSparks 2011 is such competition for those aspiring young minds who are like a sponge, ready to soak up game and apply it to their own experience. Sparks, the paper presentation contest of Avishkar''11 aims at tapping this infinite potential of young mind to generate an idea, which when  given a proper platform, can transform into a path breaking discovery. We invite you to bring forth such original ideas and present it in a genuine and comprehensive way. The idea may be anything ranging from a new diode, which never breaks down to an ingenious technique of optimizing database in the clouds of computing.\r\n<br>\r\n<b>"Last date of submission of sparks extended from 15th Sept to 17th Sept"</b><br></p><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('sparks', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br>The canons are<br><br>\r\n<ul><li>All the participants have to register themselves online.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>Teams can have a maximum of 3 participants.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>At least one member from all participating teams must be a student of Electrical or Electronics engineering and applied disciplines.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>Participants could be from any year and any institute. Participants from different institutes may form a team provided their college administration allows them.<br><br></li><li>For Paper Presentation, the topic of the paper should be based on emerging / advance technology and recent developments in the respective branch of Engineering.\r\n\r\n<br><br></li><li>You are free to submit any number of abstracts but only one would be considered for presentation and the selection lies with the organizing team.\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><br></li><li>Author and coauthor must be bonafied student of technical institute.\r\n<br><br></li><li>One paper will be presented by only one author.\r\n<br><br></li><li>At least one author, who will present the paper, has to register the event and send details of their team to <b><a href="mailto:spark.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">spark.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b> .\r\n\r\n<br><br></li><li>Certificate will be issued to participant, who has registered the event and presented the paper.\r\n\r\n<br><br></li><li>Prizes and certificates will be given to the best presentation based on the criteria decided by the judges.<br><br></li><li>Submit the abstract in standard format given on the website.<br><br></li>\r\n</ul>', 'y'),
('embedded_design', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br>\r\n<h4 align="center">"Know how to take what could be, \r\nand make it what is."\r\n\r\n</h4><br><br><br>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/embedded_design.jpg" width="50%" align="left"  alt="embedded_design"></img>\r\nAs embedded systems get more and more complex, designers need a way to specify them in an effective and non-ambiguous manner. This is especially important when part of the development is done by different teams or subcontracted to other companies.<br><br>\r\nEmbedded systems are designed to do some specific task, rather than be a general-purpose computer for multiple tasks. Some also have real-time performance constraints that must be met, for reasons such as safety and usability; others may have low or no performance requirements, allowing the system hardware to be simplified to reduce costs.<br><br>\r\nThe program instructions written for embedded systems are referred to as firmware, and are stored in read-only memory or Flash memory chips. They run with limited computer hardware resources: little memory, small or non-existent keyboard and/or screen.<br><br>\r\nEmbedded controllers are often the heart of an industrial control system or a process control application. They may also be at the center of a portable data acquisition system or remote controller that allows an application to keep running even if its umbilical link to the outside world is cut.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><br> </p>\r\n<p align="center"><a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dEYyT0x4MlhReHhCMU9TZFBycDczdFE6MQ" target="_blank"><b>Click here to Register</b></a></p><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('embedded_design', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ol><li>There can be a maximum of 3 members in the same team. The members of the team need not be from the same institution. All members should be current students of a recognized educational institution. All teams and their members should register themselves online, failing which, their participation in the final rounds will not be considered.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>The competition shall consist of two rounds. The first round, the preliminaries,\r\n      will  consist of the submission of an abstract that details the approach adopted   by the team towards solving the problem and any progress made already. The abstract should clearly outline the following details:  <br><br>\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Team details (members and their institutions, contact details including phone numbers and email addresses of each member and team name).<br><br></li><li>Brief introduction to the problem statement (to test your understanding of what is required).<br><br></li><li>Your approach towards solving the problem, including design decisions as well as technical details.<br><br></li><li>Work already completed (in which case a snapshot of current code is required).<br><br></li><li>Estimated time of completion.<br><br></li><li>Any other comments.<br><br></li></ul></li>\r\n\r\n<li>The final round of the competition will consist primarily of a presentation by the team, involving the following: <br><br>\r\n<ul><li>Design decisions and implementation details.<br><br></li><li>A test run on the reference software.<br><br></li><li>A viva round.<br><br></li><li>Any other specific request made by the judges.<br><br></li></ul></li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Any kind of plagiary will lead to disqualification from ELECTROMANIA 2K11.\r\n\r\n<br><br></li><li>Mail ur abstracts to <b><a href="mailto:embeddeddesign.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">embeddeddesign.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b>.<br><br>\r\nThe deadline for abstract submission is 11:59pm, 10th Sept, 2011.<br><br><bbr>\r\n</li></ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Judging Criteria</b><br><br>\r\n\r\nJudging will be done by faculty members of Electrical and Electronics department.<br><br>\r\nThe teams will be awarded points on the following aspects by the judges: <br><br>\r\n<ul><li>Design decisions and implementation.<br><br></li><li>Presentation and viva.<br><br></li><li>Additional points.<br><br></li></ul>\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
('impromptu', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br>\r\n<h4 align="center">The very best circuits are those that are designed well in advance.\r\n</h4><br><br><br>\r\n<p align="justify">	<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/impromtu.jpg" width="50%" align="left"  alt="impromtu"></img>\r\nThe very basic knowledge of gates and other electronics hardware, backed by your thinking ability can\r\neasily propel you to the zenith of electronics design.\r\n\r\nImpromptu is an on the spot hardware designing contest aimed to develop your practical application in\r\nelectronics domain. You will have to physically realize the circuits some of which may be basic and some\r\nmay require a bit of brain storming from your side.\r\n\r\n<br><br><br><br><br> </p><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('impromptu', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ol type="1"><li>A team of maximum 2 members are allowed from any branch of second and third year.</li><br>\r\n<li>If any one of the team member belongs to third year, then that team will be considered in third year            \r\n   Category.</li><br>\r\n\r\n<li> Only those who qualify first round will be allowed for 2nd round.</li><br>\r\n<li> Winning criteria in 2nd round will be as follows:-\r\n<ol type="a"><li>\r\nNumber of problems solved within stipulated time.</li>\r\n<li>optimised hardware on the basis of cost and time.</li></ol></li><br>\r\n<li>Judges decision will be final.</li><br>\r\n<li>Any kind of unfair means will lead to disqualification of the team.</li><br>\r\n<li>The students must be present with valid identity cards at the time of event.</li><br>\r\n<li>Any kind of plagiary will lead to disqualification from ELECTROMANIA 2K11.</li><br>\r\n<li> You need to register yourself for the event at <a href="mailto:impromptu.avishkar2k11@gmail.com"><b>impromptu.avishkar2k11@gmail.com </b></a>to confirm your  participation in the event.</li><br>\r\n</ol><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('war_of_the_currents', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br>\r\n<h4 align="center">"scientia potentia est "...the sparks that ignited The War of Currents .\r\n</h4><br><br><br>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/war_of_currents.jpg" width="50%" align="left"  alt="war of the current"></img>\r\nWar of currents started between two pioneers ''George Westinghouse'' and ''Thomas Edison'' in the decade of 1880s due to an adversary of promoting dc current(Thomas Alva Edison) or ac current(George Westinghouse)...but the war here will be different. When you will mess with meshes of current and the glaze of voltages, the definitions of war will be altered and by wandering through the new horizons of imaginations, the solutions would be brought into realizations. The matter here is to sustain and to conquer this war.  If the practical aspects of electrical and electronics melt a special corner in your heart, you cannot afford to miss the War of the Currents!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><br></p><br><br><br><br> \r\n', 'y');
