('war_of_the_currents', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul type="disc"><li>This would be an individual event.</li><br>\r\n<li>1st year-Open for all branches.\r\nfor 2nd & 3rd year- Electronics & Electrical branches only.</li><br>\r\n<li>First round is an elimination round.</li><br>\r\n\r\n<li>There would be separate cut-offs for all three years.</li><br>\r\n<li> Decision of organizers would be final and binding.</li><br>\r\n<li> The students must be present with valid identity cards at the time of event.</li><br>\r\n<li> Any kind of plagiary will lead to disqualification from ELECTROMANIA 2K11.</li><br>\r\n<br>\r\n', 'y'),
('contraption', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br> \r\n 	\r\n    \r\n    <h4>&quot;The complexity of things - the things within things - just seems to be endless. Nothing is easy, nothing is simple.&quot;  <i>Alice Munro</i></h4><br/></br><br/>\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/contraption.jpg" width="90%"  alt="contraption"></img><br/><br/><p align="justify" > In Contraptions, there is no place for Simplicity. This Olympics of Complexity is designed to pull students away from conventional problem-solving and push them into the endless chaos of imagination and intuitive thought. . Instead of just "solving" the problem, teams have to make the solution as complicated and as convoluted as possible. A simple question "How you will pour water in a glass?" A simple answer by "pouring" simply by hands but can you do that by Deck of cards!!<br/><br/>\r\nWhat is needed is a crazy mind capable of dreaming up the most complex of answers to the simplest of tasks.<br/>\r\n<br/>&quot;<b>Everything is complicated; if that were not so, life and poetry and everything else would be a bore.</b>&quot;  <i>Stevens, Wallace\r\n</i><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></p>', 'y'),
('contraption', 4, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Open to all branches of 1st year, 2nd year and 3rd year.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Teams should consist of four members with at least one member from <u>Mechanical or Production & Industrial Engineering.</u>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Students should carry proof of identity issued by their institution.</li>\r\n<li>Prior abstract submission is necessary</li>\r\n<li>Those who are willing to participate have to send their \r\n	<ul><li>Team Name</li>\r\n    <li>Member''s name, registration number, branch, email id and contacts to <!--<a href="contraption.mechrocosm2k11@gmail.com"><b>contraption.mechrocosm2k11@gmail.com</b></a>--> cordinators email to get them registered for event.</li></ul></li></ul>', 'y'),
('veni_vidi_vici', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">"Industrial Stalwarts does not capitalise on existing theories. They give birth to it".</h4><br/></br><br/>\r\n<p align="justify" ><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/veni_vidi_vici.png" width="50%" align="left" alt="veni_vedi_veci"></img>Veni Vidi Vici is an event that that would take you to a journey where you could unravel the deepest mysteries of Industrial Engineering, Planning and Development.<br /><br />\r\nIt would give you an unparallel opportunity to tackle the real life industrial problems head-on, and come forward with creative and unique solutions.<br /><br />\r\n\r\nThis event is concerned with the development, improvement, implementation and evaluation of integrated systems of manpower, money, materials, together with the principles and methods of engineering to specify, predict, and evaluate results to be obtained from such systems or processes.<br /><br />\r\n\r\nBe ready to take the challenge ''head-on''.<br /><br />\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n', 'y'),
('veni_vidi_vici', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul ><li>Participate in a team of three.\r\nFor 1st year, it is open to all branches. For 2nd and 3rd year, at least one of the members should be from Mechanical Engineering Department.</li>\r\n<li>Prior registration for the event is mandatory</li>\r\n<li>Short listing of Teams for Final Round would be done on the basis of cumulative score of Round 1 and Round 2.</li>\r\n<li>Rules are subjected to change as per the requirement. Decision of coordinators will be final and binding.\r\n</li></ul>\r\n', 'y'),
