('treasure_war', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br><h4 align="center">A Problem on Manual Robotics</h4><br><br><p align="justify">For centuries , artistic treasures have been taken away from the lands that created them. The civilizations believe that these treasures will bring back the ancient death grip they brought to their owners. <br><br>\r\n\r\nNow rivals, the race to the treasure begins. Two of the stalwart rivals send their congruously trained bots to the most precious treasure of all times. The treasure is locked beneath a stem of pipe, encased in which is a mechanism to unlock the\r\ntreasure. A mysterious gate guards the land where treasure belongs. To enter into the land, you need to unlock the gate using two magical keys. yeah rite!!, the keys are magical, they act as a shield to the bot they belong. No folks! not over yet.. :). The dapper guardians of the treasure have put dodgy hurdles over the course . <br><br>\r\n\r\nMoreover, getting the keys is not that facile, as you will see. And hey!! Getting them is not the end of it. The other bot can hit you to take them. Hmm, sounds interesting!!, isn''t it ? Man!! do I need to tell you, the bots have a limited life? Bingo!! you can take the whole life of your opponent and obtain the pleasure of completing entire task without any hindrance :P. Bullets are provided in appropriate numbers over the whole course. There is a secret "POWER BULLLET" as well somewhere along the course.<br><br>\r\n\r\nWHOA!! I am sure, the bots will have lots of fun, fighting for the treasure.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/treasure_wars.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="Treasure Wars"></img>\r\n\r\nEach treasure bot is a explorer and fighter bot capable of moving on solid ground in any direction. Besides it has two more mechanisms,\r\nSHOOTING and GRABBING. <br><br>\r\n\r\nSHOOTING - Requires a full-fletched mechanical scheme that can shoot ping pong balls.<br><br>\r\n\r\nGRABBING - Can grab a ping pong ball, and\r\n a cylinder(dimensions will be released soon)<br><br>\r\n\r\nKEY GRABBING MECHANISM - Based on key specifications.<br><br>\r\n\r\nNOTE : Speed is the key.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>\r\n</p>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>TASKS TO BE PERFORMED :</b><br><br>\r\n<ol type="1">\r\n<li>Diffuse Mines by dropping a Ball into the mine area. (10 points)<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Grab Key 1(Virtual Key). (20 points)<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Grab the cylinder to unlock the key2. (10 points)<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Fix the cylinder at given place to unlock key2. (10 points)<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Grab key 2. (30 points)<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Place the  wedge to climb up the altar. (50 points)<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Unlock the treasure. (75 points)<br><br></li></ol>\r\n\r\n<b><center>BUZZINGA!! YOU HAVE DONE IT. GO PARTY!</center></b><br><br>\r\n<b>NOTE : </b><br><br>\r\n<ol type="1">\r\n<li>Shooting ordinary balls - Each ball reduces 10% life.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Shooting special black ball -  reduces 25% of life.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Entering mines without diffusing me - reduces 10% of life.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Damaging arena will reduce points.(can lead to elimination).  <br><br></li></ol><br>Last date for submission of abstract is 19th September, 9:00PM to <a href="mailto:r.p.gond2008@gmail.com">r.p.gond2008@gmail.com</a><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p align="center"><a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dExFR3Jsb3RJSllJaHJaS3lsMk4wYXc6MQ" target="_blank"><b>Click here to Register</b></a></p><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('survivor_series', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">Survie du plus fort</h4><br/></br><br/>\r\n<p align="justify" ><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:10px" src="events/survivor_series.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="survivor_series"></img>To start with, lets see if you know these<br/><br/>\r\n<b>Why does a tube light flicker before glowing??<br/>\r\nHow do goggles make you see 3-D effect in a movie??<br/>\r\nHow a cigarette lighter produces sparks??<br/>\r\nWhat does "bone" in bone china refer to??<br/></b><br/><br/>\r\nThink you know the answer to ''em all ?? Well if you do then just come up\r\nand show us how much more. If you don''t ,then we say there''s no harm in\r\nlearning either (frankly speaking you must know atleast two of the above\r\n:P).There is a plethora of such small real life processes and mechanisms that\r\nwe must know about (we''re supposedly gonna be engineers, right?? :P).\r\nSo we provide you with a perfect symposium to come up and show if you\r\nhave it in you to be a good "engineer".<br/>\r\n<br></p><br><br>', 'y'),
('cadwalk', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">An Adventure of FUN ...to do the Impossible.</h4>\r\n<br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify" ><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/cad_venture.gif" width="50%" align="left" alt="cad_venture"></img>Design is the creative, iterative and often open-ended process of conceiving and developing components, systems and processes. Design requires the integration of engineering, basic and mathematical sciences to practical ends such as the design, manufacture, and operation of efficient and economical structures, machines, processes, and systems in a systematic way.<br/><br/>\r\nCAD is the modelling of physical systems on computers via softwares like PRO-E, AUTOCAD etc.It allows both interactive and automatic analysis of design variants, and the expression of designs in a form suitable for manufacturing. So gear up to explore and mold your creativity and analytics into this virtual designing event and add a new dimension to the existing.</p>\r\n', 'y'),
('cadwalk', 3, 'Rules', '<br /><br />\r\n<ol type="1">\r\n<li>There will be separate competition for each, 1st, 2nd and 3rd yr students.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Utmost two participants, in each team, are allowed from 1st and 2nd yr team and individual participation is permitted from 3rd yr.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Participants must be either from Mechanical or from Production branch.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Problems for 1st year students will be based on AUTOCAD and 2nd & 3rd yr participants will be allowed to use any CAD software apart from AUTOCAD for eg: PRO-E, CATIA etc. But all participants need to consult the respective coordinators regarding the permission to work on the software other then the two mentioned above.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Round 1 problem should include\r\n<ul><li>Details of the problem on word document pertaining to real life feasibility, cost structure, material details, manufacturing process i.e how much closer they can approach to a real life modeling of the product. (not for 1st yr)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The solution of the problem on CAD software.<br /><br /></li></ul></li>\r\n<li>Originality is highly expected. No design should be copied.</li><br /><br /></ol>\r\n\r\n<b>Judging Criteria:</b><br /><br />\r\n<ul><li>innovation - a new feature is added to the existing designs such as new working mechanism or an entirely new model.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>creativity - intricate design i.e reaching to the smallest part possible.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>designing accuracy, software knowledge.<br /><br /></li></ul>\r\n<br/><br/>', 'y'),
('survivor_series', 2, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\nIt''s all about "survival of the fittest" (yeah thats what survie du plus fort\r\nmeans if at all you were wondering: D).<br><br>\r\nSo whoever survives till the end of the following three rounds emerges as a\r\nwinner.<br><br><br>\r\n<b>Round 1 :</b> "HOW stuff works"<br><br>\r\nThe name says it all. This is about how things work, be it a pencil or even a\r\nlock and key. The more you know, the better is your chance of survival.\r\nThis will be written round comprising questions from "General\r\nEngineering" and "General Aptitude".<br><br>\r\nP.S.: It does not matter how many books you''ve read. All thats gonna help\r\nyou here is what you already know. The better you''ve observed things\r\naround you, the more you get to score.<br><br><br>\r\n<b>Round 2: "Break ''em all"</b><br><br>\r\nHave you ever wondered what goes inside a machine?<br><br>\r\nHow so many intricate components fall into place to form a compact\r\nmachine?<br><br>\r\nOr how do these components work in tandem to perform the specific\r\nfunction?<br><br>\r\nWell this is what we''ll put you through.<br><br>\r\n<b>"Reverse engineer"</b> a machine we give you and tell us how it works.<br><br>\r\nP.S.: At the end of this round, you will surely know everything about that\r\nmachine atleast.<br><br>\r\n<b>Round 3:"POWER ''the'' POINT"</b><br><br><br>\r\nConvince a panel of judges over a given topic through a PowerPoint\r\npresentation.<br><br>\r\nP.S.: Extensive research and good arguments will definitely win you more\r\npoints.<br><br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b><br><br>\r\nThis event is all about mixing fun with knowledge. You will be truly\r\namazed that there are so many things you never even thought about. And at\r\nthe end of the event you will surely leave with lots of knowledge to take\r\nhome.<br><br>\r\n<b>Disclaimer:</b><br><br>\r\nAll that we said above is partially false.<br><br>\r\nThis event is all about fun.<br><br>\r\nSo just be there and enjoy yourself!!!!<br><br>\r\nAnd if you think this event is for the geeks, be ready to be surprised at the\r\nend.<br><br>', 'y'),
('triathlon', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">PATH TO INNOVATION</h4><br/></br><br/>\r\n<p align="justify" ><b>"Any intelligent fool can make things bigger and more complex... It takes a touch of genius - and a lot of courage to move in the opposite direction." <i>Albert Einstein </i>\r\n</b>\r\n<br/><br/><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/triathlon.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="triathlon"></img>\r\nDischarging duties doesn''t depend on your technical competence alone. It also involves your capability to work in groups, to bear pressure and to be able to deliver what is expected from you. Rather than a technical geek, the aim should be to develop a person who can survive the most hectic situation without any sign of break off or fatigue.\r\nHere the budding technocrats will be analysed for what they are made up of.\r\n\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('triathlon', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<b>It is an individual event.</b><br><br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Round 1 will be held before Avishkar and Round 2 and 3 will be held during Avishkar.</li>\r\n<li>Each Round will be an elimination round.</li>\r\n<li>The Technical test for 1st, 2nd and 3rd year students will be different.</li>\r\n<li>For third year students there will be a separate technical and aptitude cut-off.</li>\r\n<li>Decision of Coordinators will be final and binding.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
('thematica', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">"If all think alike then no one is thinking"</h4><br/><br/></br>\r\n<p align="justify" ><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events//thematica.png" width="50%" align="left" alt="Thematica"></img>It''s time to go for a different and innovative way of thematic thinking to deal with the current problems and come out with the smart solution.<br/><br/>\r\nThematica is a Paper Presentation event to invite your original ideas and findings about a practical problem.<br/><br/>\r\nThe aim is to explore and understand various perspectives and ideas in order to get a broad insight into different aspects of knowledge.<br/><br/>\r\nWhat you need to do is just bring some innovative means to solve any one of the problems which is cost effective and feasible.\r\n\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('thematica', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul >\r\n<li>Open for all branches( At least one member should form MED)</li><li>\r\nTeam of three (All members should be from the same year of engineering)</li><li>\r\nOne team can give solution to only one problem </li><li>\r\nSolution to the problem suggested should be well supported by science.</li><li>\r\nAbstract should contain the following:\r\n<ul><li>Solution to the problem</li><li>\r\nDesign/ Methodology/Approach</li><li>\r\nFeasibility and cost effectiveness</li><li>\r\nPaper Limitation</li><li>\r\nPractice Limitation</li><li>\r\nReferences</li></ul></li>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>The idea should not be a summer project of someone and should not be the one which is already published in some journal.</b></ul>\r\n', 'y'),
('mechrosoft', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">SOFT CORNER OF MECHANICAL</h4><br/></br><br/>\r\n<p align="justify" ><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/mechrosoft.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="mechrosoft"></img> As mechanical engineering begins to merge with other disciplines the need to utilize new computer skills into the existing design and analysis processes to find better and innovative solutions to problems is increasing. It demands error free analysis with deep attention to the smallest detail. Further the time is another constraint. So call forth your metal powers and computer skills for you shall need them to crack the running time and problems.<br/>\r\nMechrosoft is a programming event in which problems relating to mechanical engineering will be given to you and to solve that you have to make use of programming languages like C, C++ or MATLAB.\r\n</p>\r\n', 'y'),
('mechrosoft', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul>\r\n<li>This is a team event comprising of two members, one member must be from Mechanical Engineering Department.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>Program must be either in C, C++ or MATLAB. MATLAB will be preferred.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>You have to submit program''s soft copy and hard copy along with algorithm and solution of the problem to the undersigned.<br>\r\n  <br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>If anyone found copying the programs, the team(s) will be immediately disqualified.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>Solutions of Problems should be submitted by given deadline date.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>Rules are subjected to change as per the requirements. Decision of coordinators will be final and binding.<br><br></li>\r\n</ul><br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Judging parameters:</b><br><br>\r\n<ul><li>Approach of the participants in solving the problems.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in using C, C++ or MATLAB to solve practical engineering problems.<br><br></li></ul><br><br>\r\n ', 'y'),
('power_stroke', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">PATH TO INNOVATION</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="jusify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:10px" src="events/power_stroke.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="power_stroke"></img>"Scientists discover that which already is;\r\nEngineers create that which has never been"<br/><br/>\r\nCreativity, as has been said, consists largely of rearranging what we know in order to find out what we do not know. If you are not much certain about what was just said, "POWER STROKE" will surely change your outlook. Basic idea of this event is to bring out the innovator that has been dormant inside all of us since long and has been craving for an opportunity to get noticed.<br/><br/>\r\nPower Stroke is ''A Paper Presentation'' event of Avishkar 2K11, MNNIT for upcoming engineers for proving them how innovative they are. You don''t need to be a research scholar with an elaborate profile for participating in this event. Here the task is\r\nsimple. Come up with a new innovative idea, prove to the people out there that it will contribute to the world in some or the other, and that is feasible and cost effective too. So explore your little innovator and land up here.\r\n</p>\r\n', 'y'),
('power_stroke', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul><li>Open to all branches.\r\n</li><br><li>Team of two (both members should be from the same year of engineering).\r\n</li><br><li>Idea suggested should be well supported by science.\r\n</li><br><li>Idea can be related to any topic ranging from General science, Physics, Mechanical\r\nEngineering, Chemistry, Biotechnology and even Mathematics.\r\n</li><br><li>Abstract should contain the following:\r\n</li><br><li>Purpose of the paper\r\n</li><br><li>Design/ Methodology/Approach\r\n</li><br><li>Finding\r\n</li><br><li>Feasibility and cost effectiveness\r\n</li><br><li>Paper Limitation\r\n</li><br><li>Practice Limitation\r\n</li><br><li>References\r\n</li><br><li>Abstract should be in not more than 500 words\r\n</li><br><li>Lastly....... we also use Google......try to give us an innovative idea.</li></ul>\r\n', 'y'),
('concube', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">To express is to drive, And when you want to give something presence,You have to consult nature, This is where DESIGN comes in.</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/concube.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="concube"></img>ConCube is an event which involves the use of concrete and various concreting techniques for creating that perfect material which forms the backbone of all major structures.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p>', 'y'),
('concube', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul>\r\n<li>This is a team event. Each team can have up to 4 members. \r\n<br><br></li><li>All the members should be of Civil engineering branch.\r\n<br><br></li><li>At least 1 member must be from 2nd or 3rd year.\r\n<br><br></li><li>No student can be a part of more than one team.</li></ul>\r\n', 'y'),
('crossover', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">Bridges are the path of civilization,\r\nit walks through them...\r\n</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/crossover.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="crossover"></img>CROSSOVER is an on the spot event, Where you have to design, estimate, and build an economical, artistic model of a bridge to best suit the specified situation. It''s time to connect your imaginations to reality.<br><br><br><br><br></p>', 'y'),
('crossover', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<ul><li>A team will consist of maximum 5 members.  <br><br></li>\r\n<li>The event is open for all branches provided that there should be a minimum \r\nof 3 civil students in a team. <br><br></li><li>\r\nThere will be a total of four prizes including prize for best innovative design, \r\nprovided that the truss satisfy all the constraints. \r\n<br><br></li><li>Trusses other than K-Truss would be preferred. \r\n<br><br></li><li>Once the structure is weighed, you are not allowed to modify your structure \r\nin any way. \r\n<br><br></li><li>If the structure fails to satisfy any of the above constraints then  it will be \r\nsummarily rejected. \r\n<br><br></li><li>Any team that is not ready at the time specified will be disqualified \r\nimmediately. \r\n<br><br></li><li>Judges'' decision shall be final and binding on all \r\n<br><br></li><li>The whole event is divided into two stages:- <br><br>\r\n<b> PRELIMINARY STAGE </b><br><br>\r\n<ul><li>All the teams are required to submit a design sketch  and a brief analysis of the bridge truss  \r\n<br><br></li><li>For the analysis part, you may take assistance of  STAAD-PRO  or  any other convenient \r\nsoftware or can solve manually <br><br></li><li>\r\nJudging criterion for the preliminary stage will be based on your submitted design, analysis \r\nand the expected load which the structure can support <br><br></li><li>\r\nThere are points for aesthetics and originality as well <br><br></li></ul></li>\r\n<b> FINAL STAGE </b><br><br>\r\n<ul><li>All the selected teams will have to come at MNNIT campus for constructing their bridges <br><br></li><li>\r\nAll the materials will be provided and you have to build the whole structure in the allotted time <br><br></li><li>\r\nThe bridge will be evaluated for its strength as failure-load to self-weight ratio (efficiency). \r\n<br><br></li><li>The final winners will be selected on the basis of the efficiency and other bonus points. \r\n<br><br></li><li>vThere will be a viva related to one''s understanding of bridge <br><br>\r\n                <center><b> Efficiency = weight sustained before failure/self-weight of the structure </b></center><br><br></li></ul><br><center>\r\n \r\nFor any queries contact us at <b><a href="mailto:crossover2k11@gmail.com">crossover2k11@gmail.com </a></b>  \r\nor contact the event coordinators </center>', 'y'),
('carpediem', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br><h4 align="center">\r\n"Seize the Day from others, putting as little trust as possible in the future. As future is unforeseen."</h4><br><br><br>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/carpe_diem.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="carpediem"></img>Carpe Diem is an individual event which will measure the power and capability inside you to seize the day for you. Ability will be judged on the basis of your technical and aptitude skills. The event solely meant to measure your knowledge and  position in World Of Civilians.  So Reinforce your brain and get ready to present the Civilian inside you and earn the tag of CARPE DIEM.<br><br></p>\r\n', 'y'),
('carpediem', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Its an individual participating event.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Open to all branches for 1st year students only.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Open to Civil Engineering branch student for 2nd and 3rd year.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Only MNNIT Students can participate.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Anybody found breaking rules or violating instructions given, will be debarred from CARPE DIEM.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Decision of coordinators will be final, no queries regarding rechecking will be entertained.</li></ul>\r\n', 'y'),
('arpenteur', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">The past is history, the future is a mystery, and this moment is the gift, that is why this moment is called the present.<br/>\r\nNothing is too small to know and nothing is too big to attempt.</h4><br/><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/arpenteur.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="arpenteur"></img>This is a field surveying event.Are you good at picking up the trail with a single clue??? Then you have come to the right place... An ''X'' never marks the spot, this is no other quotidian thing, and lets test how efficacious you are to unveil the enigma at end of which awaits booty.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p>', 'y'),
('arpenteur', 3, 'Rules', '<br /><br />\r\n<ul><li>Each group will consist of 4 members.<br /><br /></li><li>\r\nAt least 3 members should be from CIVIL ENGINEERING\r\n<br /><br /></li><li>Members can be of any year.\r\n<br /><br /></li><li>No other instruments then the ones specified on will be provided in the final round.\r\n<br /><br /></li><li>Any kind of plagiary will lead to disqualification.\r\n<br /><br /></li><li>Decision of judges will be final and binding to all.</li></ul>\r\n', 'y'),
('softbuild', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">Engineering problems are under-defined, there are many solutions, good, bad and indifferent. The art is to arrive at a good solution. This is a creative activity, involving imagination, intuition and deliberate choice.\r\n\r\n</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/soft_build.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="soft_build"></img>In this you will have to analyse the real life civil engineering problems with the aid of computers by developing the programming codes and usage of specific softwares.Tackle the problems with sobriety in your judgment.<br><br><br><br><br></p>', 'y'),
('softbuild', 3, 'Rules', '<br /><br />	<ol type="1"><li>Each team can have a maximum of three members with at least one being from civil engineering branch.</li><br />\r\n<li>Use of calculators or books is NOT permitted in the final round.</li><br />\r\n<li>	Submission of Codes for the elimination round after the deadlines will not be entertained.</li><br />\r\n<li>Decision of the judges will be final.</li><br />\r\n<li>The last date for submission of Round 1 Problems is <b>21<sup>st</sup> September, 2011.</li><br /></ol><br /><br /></b>\r\n<center><a href="http://tinyurl.com/3g8q5u3" target="_blank">Click here to register your team.</a></center>', 'y'),
('aashiyana', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">The houses of the holy, the temple of your soul Surrounding you is the celestial splendor built on a once barren uninhabited patch of land..If you cant leave your dreams, at least live in them..You have to build the house, where they will build their home..</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/aashiyana.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="aashiyana"></img>This is an event in which the imagination and knowledge of structures and architechture will be involved to create a model house for a specific conditions.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p>', 'y'),
('aashiyana', 4, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Each team must consist of at least 2 and maximum 4 members.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>No branch or year restriction is there for team formation.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Participants from outside MNNIT can participate simply by coming with their plan and material required for their design.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Students have to bring their own materials for making the models.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>No material will be provided by us.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Teams won''t be allowed to participate with readymade models.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Judges decision will be final and binding on all.<br><br></li></ul>\r\n', 'y'),
('avantgarde', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4><i><center>It refers to people or works that are experimental or innovative, particularly with respect to art, culture, and politics. And being a civil engineer is all about using your imagination, and creating something n providing ideas which can help the world move in a better way. Avant Garde is all about putting your innovative idea onto paper and justifying it. So, start scratching your heads, use your acumen, and bring forward your ideas to showcase it.</center></i></h4><br /><br /><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/avant_garde.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="avant_garde"></img>AVANT GARDE is a paper presentation event. The topic for the paper presentation can be anything which is related to the field of civil engineering.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></p>', 'y'),
('avantgarde', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul><li>Teams will consist of maximum 2 members. One member must  be from Civil Engineering branch.\r\n<br><br></li><li>For 1st year''s students there is no branch restriction.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Each team would be given maximum 15 minutes for presentation.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Idea should be feasible, original and should be related to civil engineering.\r\n<br><br></li><li>''Cut and copied'' ideas may lead to disqualification.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Judge''s decision will be final and binding to all.</li>\r\n<li>Last date for abstract submission 18 September 2011.</li></ul>\r\n', 'y'),
('vortex', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">Whatever the mind can conceive and believe, the mind can achieve.\r\n\r\n</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/vortex.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="vortex"></img>Bag your basics and prepare yourself for a voyage to fight the power crisis in today''s era. Water has been our favorite toy from the very 1st day of our life. Its time to play with water again. Whirlpool your knowledge of hydraulics to win !!!<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p>', 'y'),
('vortex', 4, 'Rules', '<br /><br /><ol type="1"><li>A team can have a maximum of three members.</li><br />\r\n<li>At least one member should be from civil engineering branch.</li><br />\r\n<li>No year restriction is there in team formation.</li><br /></ol>\r\n', 'y'),
('bio_vision', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">Welcome to the WET LAB!\r\n</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/biovision.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="biovision"></img>Tired of poring over your heavy text books every day? Is the double helix of DNA no longer as interesting as it appeared in the first lecture of molecular biology? Do Mendel''s laws not appeal to you as much as they did to him?<br/><br/>\r\nIf yes, then it''s high time you take a break! In BIOVISION we urge you to enter the real world of biotechnology. Let the books decorate your shelf for a day! Let the pen rest on your table! Put on the lab coat, grab a pipette and revitalize your senses!\r\n\r\n\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('bio_vision', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<ul><li>The event is open only to second and third year students of Biotechnology branch in M.N.N.I.T Allahabad.</li>\r\n<li>A team can have a maximum of 3 members.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>The team should consist of at least one member from 2<sup>nd</sup> year and one member from 3<sup>rd</sup> year.In case you are not able to form a team with your senior/junior, do come up for the event we shall form teams there by random selection.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>For any further queries mail us : <a href="genesis.avishkar2k11@gmail.com"><b>genesis.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b></li></ul>\r\n', 'y'),
('bio_vision', 4, 'FAQ', '<br><br>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 1.</td><td> Where to start? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> This event  is all about your laboratory knowledge. So just brush up your lab skills and  revise the principles of instrumentation.  </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 2.</td><td> Will the  viva be based solely on my final experiment? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> It will  mainly be based on the allotted experiment but revising the basics would help. </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 3.</td><td> Is it  compulsory to team up with a student of some other year? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px" >Ans:</td><td> Yes</td></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n  <td width="50px">Q 4.</td>\r\n  <td> Please elaborate more on the treasure hunt round? Is it an elimination round?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Yes, it''s an elimination round. After each clue, a fixed number of teams will move to the next clue, depending upon how much time you take to solve it. <br><br>\r\nRegarding the treasure hunt, you better wait and watch! Don''t worry; it won''t require very deep technical knowledge.\r\n </td></tr>\r\n</table><br/><br/>', 'y'),
('adrenaline_rush', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">Buzz right perception for perfection!!!\r\n</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/adrenaline_rush.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="adrenaline_rush"></img>\r\nSet your adrenaline racing,<br/>\r\n<br/>New challenges you''ll be facing,<br/><br/>\r\nAnalyze, think and innovate,<br/><br/>\r\nBe a savior before it''s too late.<br/><br/>\r\nDesign ideas; prove your Industrial wit,<br/><br/>\r\nCome, be a perfectionist.<br><br/>Adrenaline Rush problem statement of Round 1 is releases on 15th Sept @ 9PM<br/></p>\r\n', 'y'),
('adrenaline_rush', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul><li>\r\nIt is a team event open to all branches.\r\n<br><br></li><li>	A single team can have a maximum of 3 members.\r\n<br><br></li><li>	One member in every team must be from biotechnology. This rule does not apply for first year students.\r\n<br><br></li><li>	Participants are allowed to bring books of their choice for the second round.\r\n<br><br></li><li>For any further queries mail us :<b><a href="mailto:adrenaline.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">adrenaline.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b></li></ul><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('robocop_the_saviour', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br><h4 align="center">ROBOCOP<br>A PROBLEM ON AUTONOMOUS ROBOTICS</h4><br><br>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/robocop.jpg" width="50%" align="left"  alt="SPY-BOT pick"></img>A national security lab is under operation for making nuclear weapons to safeguard the nation. But certain terrorists with a destructive mindset have infiltrated into the country with a motive to get access to the research work being carried out at the lab. The terrorists have somehow managed to get into the lab and have inappropriately handled the weapons. As a result, there has been a radioactive leak and hence, it is humanely impossible to distinguish between the scientists and the terrorists. So the terrorists are all set to steal away important details and are about to leave soon after killing the scientists.<br><br>\r\nGet up to the challenge and catch the culprits by designing an autonomous robot which identifies them. The terrorists are to be caught and hostages have to be rescued!!<br><br></p><br><br>\r\n<b>TASK:</b><br><br>\r\n\r\n<ol type="1"><li>Teams have to build a fully autonomous robot which should be able to a traverse on a grid identified by white strips on a black background.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The robot should be capable of differentiating between two types of blocks (terrorists and scientists) lying in the radiation zone. <br><br></li>\r\n<li>The grid solving autonomous robot should be capable of detecting and transporting the blocks from the radiation zone to their respective zone.<br><br></li>\r\n</ol><br />\r\n<p align="center"><a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dHM3dHdJX09Hc1JPdGNLQzRZMkhxLXc6MQ" target="_blank"><b>Click to Register </b></a></p><br><br>', 'y'),
('clairvoyance', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">"If we knew what it was we were doing,<br/> it would not be called research, would it?"\r\n</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"> <img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/clairvoyance.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="clairvoyance"></img>Got some vague idea in your head, but never got a chance to put it into words? If yes, then you have come to the right place! In CLAIRVOYANCE, we implore you to rediscover yourself in an entirely new way. Think beyond the obvious! Merge the facts with the abstract and let that jaded imagination come back to life!<br/><br/>\r\nRemember! Every new idea looks crazy at first!<br><br><br><br><br>\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('clairvoyance', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<ul><li>The event is open to all first year students irrespective of their branches. For second and third year students at least one student in the team must be of Biotechnology branch.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>For outside participants, only undergraduate students are allowed.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>A team can have a maximum of 2 members.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>For the first round, the abstracts should be sent to<b> <a href="mailto:clairvoyance.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">clairvoyance.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b> in .doc, .docx or .pdf format having a maximum of 250 words.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The final power point presentation and viva-voce will be of 10(+2) minute''s duration.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>For any further queries mail us: <a href="genesis.avishkar2k11@gmail.com"><b>genesis.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b><br><br></li></ul>', 'y'),
('anveshans', 3, 'Problem Stetement', '	<br><br>\r\n   <ul><li><a href="./events/anveshans_problem1.pdf" target="_blank">Problem Statement 1</a><br><br></li>\r\n   <li><a href="./events/anveshans2.pdf" target="_blank">Problem Statement 2</a><br><br></li>\r\n   <li><a href="./events/anveshans3.pdf" target="_blank">Problem Statement 3</a><br><br></li>\r\n    <li><a href="./events/anveshans4.pdf" target="_blank">Problem Statement 4</a><br><br></li>\r\n<li><a href="./events/anveshans5.doc" target="_blank">Problem Statement 5</a><br><br></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n   ', 'y'),
('cryptochrome', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">The illuminating search begins...\r\n</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"> <img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/cryptochrome.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="cryptochrome"></img>\r\nGather your thoughts..<br/>\r\nTune up your senses..<br/>\r\nYou shall need it all..<br/>\r\nWhen Cryptochrome commences !!<br/><br/>\r\n<i>Cryptochrome</i>, Biotech''s very own Online Treasure Hunt!!! It''s time to revisit the past, to link the clues, to push your thoughts to the brink and find the missing link.\r\nGoogle might be your best friend, but will it suffice to take you till the end.<br><br></p><br><br>\r\n<p align="center"><a href="./crypto/">Click here to begin</a></p>', 'y'),
('cryptochrome', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul><li>\r\nThis event is open for all.\r\n<br><br></li><li>A team can consist of a maximum of 2 members. Individual participation is also permitted.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Questions are related to biotechnology so it would help to have at least one member from the same branch.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Registration is compulsory.\r\n<br><br></li><li>The team(s) finishing at the highest level will be declared as winner(s).\r\n<br><br></li><li>In case of 2 or more teams are on highest level, Prize will be distributed among them.\r\n<br><br></li><li>No unfair means can be tolerated which includes PHP injection, Dictionary attacks and hacking or anything of this sort whatsoever.\r\n<br><br></li><li>If the teams are found to share answer amongst them, the participation of the teams concerned will be terminated without any warning.\r\n<br><br></li><li>The final discretion lies with the coordinators and administrator.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Event will end on September 24, 2011 @23:59 hours.\r\n<br><br></li><li>For any further queries mail us :<b><a href="mailto:genesis.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">genesis.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b></li></ul><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('double_helix', 2, 'Event Format', '<br /><br />Double helix is a two round mega quiz event which tests your knowledge and stimulates your brain cells for quick response. <br /><br />\r\nThe event consist of the following rounds:<br /><br />\r\n<b>1.	Preliminary round:</b><br /><br />\r\nThis will be a written round comprising of questions from basic biotechnology. This round will be an elimination round and will have differential marking for 1st year, 2nd year and 3rd year teams .<br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>2.	Second quiz round :</b><br /><br />\r\nThe selected teams will participate in this round. This round consists of various sub rounds. Teams shall be eliminated according to their performances after each of these sub-rounds. The sub-rounds will comprise of various rapid fire rounds, quizzes from video clips, puzzles, cross-words etc., all related to core biotechnology.<br /><br />\r\n', 'y'),
('paladin', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">Survival of the fittest...\r\n</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/paladin.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="paladin"></img>\r\nTo make an efficient and successful engineer it requires a lot of other things than just your technical aptitude. It requires your abilities to bear pressure, to resist fatigue, to work in groups and a lot of other factors.\r\nIt''s your overall persona that propels you ahead. So let''s check your mettle.<br><br><br><b>The written round of paladin is on 15th September from 5.45 pm in the evening. </b><br><br><br><br><br>\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('paladin', 3, 'Rules', '\r\n<br><br><ul><li>\r\nThis is an individual multi-round event.\r\n<br><br></li><li>It is open to all first year students irrespective of their branches.\r\n<br><br></li><li>For second and third year students, the participants must be of the Biotechnology branch.\r\n<br><br></li><li>There will be differential marking for 1st 2nd and 3rd year students in the first round.\r\n<br><br></li><li>You are required to come in formals with fully prepared resume and supporting certificates\r\n<br><br></li><li>For any further queries mail us :<b><a href="mailto:genesis.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">genesis.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b></li></ul><br><br>', 'y'),
('paladin', 5, 'FAQ', '<br><br>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 1.</td><td>If I know just the basics of C/C++, am I fit for  this event? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> You can definitely take part in this  event. The book <strong>Let Us C</strong> by <strong>YASHVANT KANETKAR</strong> can be referred for  any preparation.  </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 2.</td><td> Is it necessary to be dressed in formals  for the GD and the Interview round? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> Yes it is. <br>\r\n  For boys formals include Formal shirt,  Trousers, Tie and formal Shoes. Tie pins and Cuff lings are not included in the  formals. <br>\r\n  For girls formals include, cotton suits  with cotton dupatta and chudidaar.  </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 3.</td><td> Why should I participate in this very  event? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>This event shall provide you with an experience that shall help you during your placements.\r\n</td></tr>\r\n\r\n</table><br/><br/>\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
('breakthrough', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br>The event has 3 stages<br><br>\r\n<ol type="1"><li><strong>Abstract and Paper submission: </strong>Submit a brief abstract of the paper, to be presented in\r\n  single column format. The  filetype can either be a doc or pdf. The abstracts are to be mailed\r\n  to the following email id<a href="mailto: breakthrough.avishkar2k11@gmail.com"><b> breakthrough.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</b></a> with the subject as\r\n  &ldquo;ABSTRACT&rdquo; before the deadline.  The selected teams will shortly be informed via mail\r\n  which will then have to  submit a full paper (strictly adhering to the IEEE format). The\r\n  template for the paper can be  downloaded from the website.</li><br /><br>\r\n<li><strong>Preliminary Round of presentation (only for MNNIT students): </strong>This will be the screening\r\n  round for MNNIT students,  where the co-ordinators will assess your paper and presentation.\r\n  It will consist of a short  presentation, not exceeding 15 minutes per team followed by which\r\n  there will be a Questioning  round. Outside participants need not attend this round and can\r\n  skip to the 3rd round  directly.<br><br></li>\r\n<li><strong>Final Round of presentation: </strong>This will be the Final round of presentation, where you will be presenting your paper before the judges. The time  limit is same as above<br><br></li></ol>\r\n<br><br>', 'y');
INSERT INTO `tabs` (`id`, `tab_no`, `name`, `description`, `display`) VALUES
('double_helix', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">''A quiz for quizzer, and everyone else''.\r\n</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/double_helix.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="double_helix"></img>\r\nUse your grey cell <br/><br/>\r\nStrain your brain <br/><br/>\r\nHit your choice....<br/><br/>\r\nBut be quick and<br/><br/>\r\nDon''t be lame<br/><br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('double_helix', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul><li>\r\nIt is a quiz event which will be played in teams.\r\n<br><br></li><li>A single team can have a maximum of 2 members.\r\n<br><br></li><li>No team will be allowed to use any electronic devices with internet connectivity during any round of the quiz. If found indulging in any such activities, the team will be disqualified.\r\n<br><br></li><li>For any further queries mail us :<b><a href="mailto:genesis.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">genesis.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b></li></ul><br><br>', 'y'),
('chemsoft', 1, 'Introduction', '</br><br/><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:60px" src="events/chemsoft.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="chemsoft"></img><p align="justify">The realm of Chemical Engineering is based on to enhancing the quality and quantity of products in an economic manner. To do this we must have an understanding about the software and control systems,which we are using in chemical industries. We recognize the need for having good analytical and software skills and bring to you ChemSoft. Participants are required to develop a software/ algorithm for a given problem.<br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/></p>', 'y'),
('chemsoft', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<ul><li>All participants should register themselves to <b><a href="mailto:chemsoft.rasayans2k11@gmail.com">chemsoft.rasayans2k11@gmail.com</a></b>  by sending a mail containing Team name, name of the participants and contact details.<br><br></li> \r\n<li>This is a team event comprising of a maximum of "three members". At least one member must be from ''Chemical Engineering Department''.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Program must be either in MS Excel or in Mat lab. Mat lab will be the preferred medium.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>You have to submit the program''s soft copy and hard copy along with the algorithm.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>If anyone is found copying the programs, the team(s) will be immediately disqualified.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The teams have to submit their solutions by 15th September 2011, after which the solution would be considered null and void.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Second Round will be held during Avishkar''11 and the rules will be declared on the spot.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Decision of coordinators will be final and binding.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>For any queries, write to us at <b><a href="mailto:chemsoft.rasayans2k11@gmail.com">chemsoft.rasayans2k11@gmail.com</a></b>.<br><br></li></ul><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('potions', 1, 'Introduction', '\r\n<br/><br/><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:60px" src="events/potions.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="potions"></img><p align="justify">One of the stellar event of Avishkar awaits you. Even the world of  Harry Potter cannot escape from Potions so how could we? Its a riddling and puzzling way to play with chemicals and know about the life. Check out the chemistry in you with your partner.<br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/></p>', 'y'),
('potions', 2, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul>\r\n<li>All participants must register themselves at <b><a href="mailto:potions.rasayans2k11@gmail.com">potions.rasayans2k11@gmail.com</a></b> by sending a mail containing Team name, name of the participants and contact details.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The event would be an ON THE SPOT EVENT and would compose  of Two rounds. The team can consist of a group of at most 2 members. At least one member must be from ''Chemical Engineering Department''.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>The <strong>1st round</strong> would be a quiz (Objective questions, Passage reading, Riddle Solving).<br><br></li><!--\r\n<li>The <strong>2nd round</strong> would involve some practical designing work in which you have to design a working model in a given time period for which the problem will be given ON THE SPOT.<br><br></li>-->\r\n<li>The <strong>2nd round</strong> would involve puzzles, anagrams and code solving relating to chemistry.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The winners of all rounds would be declared individually.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Decision of coordinators will be final and binding.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>For any queries, write to us at <b><a href="potions.rasayans2k11@gmail.com">potions.rasayans2k11@gmail.com</a></b><br><br></li></ul><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('anveshans', 1, 'Introduction', '<br/><br/><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:60px" src="events/anveshans.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="anveshans"></img><p align="justify">Ever thought of designing a chimney? Or calculating the flow of honey? Rack your brains, let the creativity and thoughts behind come forward and solve day to day problems with a bit of cleverness. Anveshans is an event in which few practical questions will be floated, giving you an opportunity to get the essence of Chemical Engineering.<br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>  </p>', 'y'),
('anveshans', 2, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul><li>\r\nAll participants must register themselves at <b><a href="mailto:anveshans.rasayans2k11@gmail.com">anveshans.rasayans2k11@gmail.com</a></b> by sending a mail containing Team name, name of the participants and contact details. <br><br></li>\r\n<li>Any undergraduate student of any discipline is eligible to participate in this event provided that one team member is from Chemical Engineering.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The team can consist of a group of at most 3 members.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Problem statements will be floated at a regular basis, and marks will be awarded on the method as well as on the final solution to the problem.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The teams have to submit their solutions by 15th September 2011, after which the solution would be considered null and void.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Participants can use any medium to find their solutions, including books, published papers, or the internet, provided a reference is provided of their sources.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>There will be a final question answer round during Avishkar''11. The questions will solely be based on the solutions provided by the teams.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>For any queries, write to us at <b><a href="mailto:anveshans.rasayans2k11@gmail.com">anveshans.rasayans2k11@gmail.com</a></b></li></ul><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('chain_reaction', 1, 'Introduction', '</br><br/><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:60px" src="events/chain_reaction.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="chain_reaction"></img><p align="justify" >What does it take to be successful?  Do you have to know all that we study in class, or do we need to be smart enough to answer logical question. Why do not you all check out the real you and where u stand in terms of intellect in crowd. Chain reaction is a quiz event which will test u in all aspects and will help u carve a niche for yourself .<br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/></p>', 'y'),
('chain_reaction', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Any undergraduate student of any discipline is eligible to participate in this event<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>Each team will have to register at <b><a href="mailto:chainreaction.rasayans2k11@gmail.com">chainreaction.rasayans2k11@gmail.com</a></b> \r\nby sending a mail containing :-<br><br>\r\n<ol type="1"><li>Team Name.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Name of the participants.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Name of the institution.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Contact details (email id and phone no.)<br><br></li></ol></li>\r\n\r\n<li>A team cosists of 2 members.<br><br></li>\r\n\r\n<li>No team is allowed to send more than one entry.<br><br></li><br><br></ul>\r\n', 'y'),
('intechxication', 1, 'Introduction', '<br/><br/><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:60px" src="events/intechxication.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="intechxication"></img><p align="justify" >Each spirit houses a <i>Chaitanya</i> but few have it in them to walk that extra mile and live past the ennui to pen those thoughts down that have the potential to revolutionize the world. Shoot the grey of your brain to the acme of creativity... enlighten the world with the sparks of a true  genius and survive to be the final gladiator left  standing, inscrutable in the arena of Shashtrartha ,revered by the rivals and coveted by the counsels... Be the one Intexticator. Pen that rasayan shastra and present the world, a paper worth preserving. <br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/></p>', 'y'),
('intechxication', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br>Any undergraduate student of any discipline is eligible to participate in this event. <br><br>\r\n<ul><li>Every participant will have to register at <b><a href="mailto:intechxication.rasayans2k11@gmail.com">intechxication.rasayans2k11@gmail.com</a></b> by sending a mail\r\ncontaining :-<br><br>\r\n<ol type="1">\r\n<li>Name of the participant.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Name of the institution.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Contact details (email id and phone number).<br><br></li></ol>\r\n<li>No one  is allowed to send more than one entry.<br><br></li></ul>', 'y'),
('live_wire', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br>Live Wire is an overnight programming contest. Problems are given in six sections:\r\n<br><br>\r\nC<br>\r\n\r\nMATLAB<br>\r\n\r\nPSPICE<br>\r\n\r\n8085 Microprocessor Programming<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Round 1 :</strong><br><br>\r\n\r\nParticipants would be given a few simple problems to solve and you need to mail the solutions in a zipped file before a deadline attached with the problem statement. The problems would be very basic in nature.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Round 2 :</strong><br><br>\r\n\r\nParticipants need to solve the problems on the spot and explain the algorithm for the same to earn points. There would be evaluators for each section and cut-offs would be decided based on the Year of the participating students. At the end of a grueling eight-hour programming race, upon fulfillment of all the cut-offs, participants with the maximum points would be declared winners. See FAQ for other queries\r\n<br><br>', 'y'),
('live_wire', 4, 'FAQS', '<br>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr><td width="52">Q 1.</td><td width="1236">. What  is the duration of the event?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="52">Ans:<br>\r\n  <br></td><td>The  event is likely to continue for six-eight hours non-stop, starting in the wee  hours of the evening and continuing till late at night.\r\n\r\n </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="52">Q 2.</td>\r\n<td >Who  is eligible to take part?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="52">Ans:<br>\r\n  <br></td><td>All  students, irrespective of their year, branch and stream, may take part in the  competition. Teams need not be necessarily from the same college and branch.<br>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="52">Q 3.</td>\r\n<td >What  other resources can I use to solve the problems?<br></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="52">Ans:<br><br>\r\n  <br><br></td><td>You  are free to bring any number of textbooks, help manuals, etc. However, use of  resources for gaining unethical advantage is a serious offence and would be  dealt with seriously; this includes getting solved examples in CDs, etc. Usage  of internet, mobile phones, pagers or any other communicating device in the  final round is prohibited and will result in disqualification.<br>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="52">Q 4.</td>\r\n<td >What  are the judging criteria?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="52">Ans:<br><br>\r\n  <br><br></td><td>In  order to make the competition fair to all participants, you''d be judged based  on the basic problem statement and consideration of special cases only.  However, readability of code might help to save some time with the evaluator  and for solving extra problems. There will be separate cut-offs on each section  for each Year</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="52">Q 5.</td>\r\n<td >What  platform would be provided to us?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="52">Ans:\r\n  <br><br><br><br><br></td><td>We  cannot guarantee the platform that would be provided but we would ensure that  no teams benefit due to undue advantage by virtue of platform used for solving  the problems. Wherever possible, the latest version of the licensed software  available with the Institute would be installed on all computers. In case of  specific doubts related to the platform of the software, please contact the coordinators  of the event.<br>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</table><br/><br/>\r\n', 'y'),
('live_wire', 5, 'Contacts', '\r\n<br><br>\r\n<table><tr height="40px">\r\n  <td width="400">Uday Jalan</td>\r\n<td width="400">+91-9454019523</td>\r\n<td width="400">udayrocks2k8@gmail.com</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height="40px">\r\n  <td width="400">Vandana  Singh</td>\r\n  <td width="400">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td width="400">vandana.picaso@gmail.com</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br><br>', 'y'),
('counter_strike', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4>"(Terrorist) F^Funk:rush b, kyle should be saving<br/> \r\n3D | miller [ 4/ 5] killed F^Warden [ 5/3] with awp <br/>\r\n3D | miller [ 5/ 5] killed F^Funk [ 6/3] with awp <br/>\r\n3D | miller [ 6/ 5] killed F^HOLDEN [ 3/4] with awp <br/>\r\n3D | miller [ 7/ 5] killed F^Torrez[st] [ 8/4] with awp <br/>\r\n3D | miller [ 8/ 5] killed F^Ph33R [ 2/3] with awp <br/>\r\n(Terrorist) F^HOLDEN:who the FUNK said to rush b? <br/>\r\n(Terrorist) F^Funk:not me..so FUNK off "</h4><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify"><br>\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:30px" align="left" src="events/counterstrike.jpg" width="50%"  alt="counterstrike"></img>\r\nIt''s terrorists v/s counter-terrorists again... And with a vengeance. Eliminate the opposite force or complete the mission objective. No mercy will be shown and there will be no retribution. If you have the WILL to KILL, then load your guns and get ready to face your fears. Prepare to strike!! It''s time for Counter Strike! gO gO gO !!!\r\n<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p><br><br><br>', 'y'),
('counter_strike', 4, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<p align="justify">Using console is strictly illegal.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;Any form of script is forbidden.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;&quot;silent bombs&quot; (i.e. the planting of a bomb which  doesn''t make a sound ) are<br>\r\n  illegal<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;Bunny hopping is allowed without script.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;Silent run is allowed without script.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;Binding &ldquo;<strong>+duck</strong>&ldquo; to the mouse wheel is forbidden.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;Using &ldquo;<strong>+duck</strong>&rdquo; behind a box is authorized.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;Only team leaders are allowed to use public in-game messages<br>\r\n  (messagemode1) within a match. The rule also applies when dead.  Use of<br>\r\n  messagemode1 by any member other than the team leader shall result  in a<br>\r\n  warning. Other team members must only use team message<br>\r\n  (messagemode2), while in a match.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;The player is deemed dead when the screen is completely faded to  black. If a<br>\r\n  bug occurs and the screen doesn&rsquo;t fade to black, the player is  deemed dead<br>\r\n  three seconds after he/she has fallen.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;Team members may communicate verbally if they are alive in the  match or<br>\r\n  when all team members are dead.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;Any player who has died cannot communicate by ANY means (No  gesture or<br>\r\n  verbal communication will be allowed) with any other team member  or<br>\r\n  opponent until the beginning of the next round.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;If a player continues to communicate after he/she is killed, the  team may be<br>\r\n  given a warning or lose by default at the referees sole  discretion.<br>\r\n  <br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;Approved Grenade Amounts Per Round<br>\r\n  &#9;&diams;&#09; Flashbangs: 2<br>\r\n  &#9;&diams;&#09; Grenades: 1<br>\r\n  &#9;&diams;&#09; Smoke Grenades: 1<br>\r\n  &#9;&diams;&#09; Video Mode :  32 Bit <br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;Default skins must be used.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;C4 must be installed at a viewable location. Installing C4 at a  location where<br>\r\n  a boost is required is NOT allowed.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;Silent C4 installation is considered bug play. Such an offense may  result in a<br>\r\n  warning or loss of all remaining TR rounds at the sole discretion  of the board<br>\r\n  of referees.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;Throwing grenades over buildings in all maps are allowed.<br>\r\n  &bull;&#09;Any use of the flash bang bug will result in a warning at the  minimum or loss<br>\r\n  by default for the offending team.<br>\r\n&bull;&#09;Watching underneath the walls is not allowed on de_train and  de_dust2.<br></p><br><br>\r\n  \r\n<h4 align="center">Warnings and Penalties</h4><br><br><br>\r\n\r\n  \r\n<p align="justify">Any  violation of the rules and restrictions given in above section during a match<br>\r\n  will  lead to any one of the following, depending solely on the decision of event<br>\r\n  coordinator.<br>\r\n   &bull;&#09;3 rounds penalty for the violating team on end score of the match.<br>\r\n   &bull;&#09;Disqualification from the event.<br><br></p><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('aoe', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">"For want of a nail, the horseshoe was lost. For want of a horseshoe, the steed was lost. For want of a steed, the message was not delivered. For want of an undelivered message, the war was lost."</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">Civilization is strange. It follows strange rules of the thumb rather than scientific principles and must be adapted to follow the environment and resources available to you. It grows and is vanquished. Only through proper strategy can one form a successful civilization. Are you the Great one to rule the world and dare to face the wrath of war? It''s time for real time strategy gaming. Welcome to the world of monolithic hegemony. Let''s quench our belligerent thirst to kill and expand.\r\n<br></p>', 'y'),
('aoe', 2, 'Rules', 'coming soon', 'n'),
('fifa', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">\r\n	Football fans of all skill levels, lace up your cleats, strap on your shin guards and step onto the\r\npitch and play professional soccer your way. FIFA 11 has arrived.\r\n</h4><br/><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/fifa.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="fifa"></img\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n	Unleash your Adrenalin to beat your Opponent. Make team chemistry visible and get rid of in\r\ngame momentum when playing a human opponent.<br/><br/>\r\nA completely new game and graphics engine brings with it a whole new level of realism and\r\ncontrol. This is as good as it gets. If you consider yourself a football fan, you absolutely can''t miss\r\nit.<br/><br/>\r\nEnjoy the freedom, make the difference<br/><br/>\r\nWE ARE 11, FIFA 11</p>\r\n    ', 'y'),
('fifa', 2, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul><li>All participants are requested to maintain good conduct & behavior at the venue throughout the duration of the tournament.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Use of abusive language and improper conduct with the member of the staff or organizer will lead to immediate disqualification.\r\n<br><br></li><li>No participants/friends will be allowed to enter the gaming area unless they are competing in the ongoing match. All other players must wait outside the lab or the place indicated by the organizers.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Participants are requested to notify the organizers if they wish to unplug any hardware from the PC to install their own.\r\n<br><br></li><li>No participants will be allowed to leave the lab until all the college equipment has been accounted for.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Participants are requested to carry their own headphones.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><br></li><li><b>Competition Method:</b> Individual plays (1 vs. 1)\r\n<br><br></li><li><b>Game Mode:</b> All Teams (Int. / Clubs) (custom Teams are not allowed)\r\n<br><br></li><li>If a player is found to be intentionally delaying the game time by passing the ball around, he may be given a warning or lose by default at the referee''s discretion.\r\n<br><br></li><li>At kickoff the ball has to be passed backwards into the player''s own half, also after every goal. \r\n<br><br></li><li>You are not allowed to score goals from within your own half. </li></ul><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('nfs', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">Need for Speed Most Wanted</h4><br/><br/><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px 0px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/nfs.jpg" width="93%"  alt="nfs" align="middle"></img><br/><br/>\r\n<p align="justify">"Shawn engages the nitrous in Han''s RX-7 and zips past a Skyline. He suddenly notices a police car parked on the left side of the road. The cops clock him at 197 kmph. ": Fast and the Furious, Tokyo Drift\r\n\r\n\r\nEngage your clavicles and fasten your seatbelts. It''s time to hit the streets. To fire your engines and push the crankshaft. To warm the rubber on polished tar. It''s time to bully the cops and break the rules. It''s time to accomplish a mission. At Avishkar 2011, Hit the gas, hold your clutches, boost up, gear yourself and drift. Just driving is not enough... I need some speed!! need for speed me</p>', 'y'),
('horizon', 1, 'Introduction', '<br/><h4 align="center">From Innovation to Enterprise</h4><br><br>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:10px" src="events/horizon.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="image is loading..."></img>Conception of any great idea is at first ridiculed, then opposed and finally looked at in awe of what it accomplished. But it takes courage to believe in your ability, your idea and your vision of what you can deliver in your business and sell it with conviction. To step out in faith - when no one else has a clue what your innovation will do never mind who will buy it. \r\nHorizon is intended as a platform where budding entrepreneurs cocooned in their shell of uncertainity test their business acumen and the future Tatas, Birlas, Ambanis of the country are born. The competition is aimed to transform the raw ideas to its fruition with multiple stages of evaluation and tough competition marking its transition into a successful Business Plan. \r\n<br><br>\r\nSo just don''t sit in front of an idea that has such great potential without ever taking action. Innovate rather than copy, stand on your own, more visible, with a unique offering you know the market needs!\r\n<br><br>\r\nSo folks if you have an idea that needs nurturing this is certainly the place to be. You shall be able to realise the full potential of your idea. And who knows these could be the first baby steps to your own future venture!\r\n<br><br>\r\n"I took the one less travelled by, And THAT has made all the difference."\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('horizon', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul><li>Students from the same institute as well as different institutes can form a team.\r\n<br><br></li><li>One team can submit only one entry.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Any team or individual cannot be a part of more than one entry.\r\n<br><br></li><li>A team can consist of a maximum of four students and at least one of them should be bonafide student of some recognized college.\r\n<br><br></li><li>There is no restriction on the number of teams from an institute.\r\n<br><br></li><li>The executive summaries have to be submitted via mail to <b><a href="mailto:horizon.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">horizon.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b>\r\n<br><br></li><li>The deadline for submission of executive summaries is September 20, 2011.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Executive summary for Round 1 should be in .pdf / .doc format , Font :-Times New Roman ,  Font Size :-12\r\n<br><br></li><li>The front page of both executive summary and complete business plan should contain the name of the business plan, college name and address, names of the participants, their mobile number and email ids. The identity of the participants should not be revealed in any other part of the document.\r\n<br><br></li><li>The organizers reserve unconditional right to disqualify an entry or cancel the participation of a team for any reason including presentation of inaccurate/incomplete information, plagiarism, late submission, or any other reason.\r\n<br><br></li><li>The time for the final presentation will be 11 minutes plus 1 minute to wind up. This will be followed by a question and answer session of 3 minutes duration.\r\n<br><br></li><li>The decision of the Judges and Event Coordinators will be final and binding.<br><br></li>\r\n</ul>', 'y'),
('biz_quizz', 1, 'Introduction', 'Coming Soon\r\n<!--<h4><center>Show how much you know (and they don''t!)</center></h4><br /><br />\r\n\r\n<p align="justify"> <img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:10px" src="events/biz_quiz.png"width="50%" align="left" alt="image loading..."></img>\r\nDo you think that you are smarter than those white collars corporate?? If you really think so, come prove us that you have the right to think so.\r\nWell this is not any quizzing session but you have to re-launch a failed product. It requires that the mistakes which we learn from the past should not be repeated and this time gets a better understanding of the customers & competition through a detailed analysis of the market forces then and now. \r\nIn the case of a product that did not do well in its first avatar, a detailed analysis of the causes that lead to the failure of the product will need to be presented and a comprehensive Marketing Strategy Document (MSD) encompassing the key areas has to be formulated. That is what biz Quiz is meant to do. So, come on and show off your way to launch the product in YOUR way.</p><br /> \r\n-->', 'n'),
('biz_quizz', 3, 'Rules', '<br /><br />There will be 2 rounds.<br /><ol type="1"> \r\n<li>Event is open to all individuals irrespective of institute, discipline and year. </li>\r\n<li> Prior registration is mandatory. </li>\r\n<li>Team should comprise of not more than three members. </li>\r\n<li>Abstract solution for Round 1 should not be more than 5 pages , Font :- Times New Roman , Font Size :- 12 </li>\r\n<li> Content should be original and not copied. </li>\r\n<li> The decision of the organisers/judges will be final and binding. </li></ol><br />\r\n\r\nYOU SHOULD MAIL YOUR ABSTRACTS AT <a href="mailto:bizquizz.avishkar2k11@gmail.com"><b>bizquizz.avishkar2k11@gmail.com   </b></a><br />\r\nLast date for submission of abstracts is 15th September 2011by 12 midnight. \r\n<br /><br />', 'n'),
('netritva', 1, 'Introduction', '<br>\r\n<h4><center>"Welcome back, Commanders !"\r\n</center></h4><br><br>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:10px" src="events/netritva.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="image is loading"></img>If you can merge the "I" with "Vie" so that it turns into the perfect "We", Netritva is just the place where you should be.<br><br>\r\nNetritva is all about the conjugation of leadership with group-spirit, cooperation with domination and needless to say, victory with handsome rewards. All you have to do is let the leader in you lead you on to the arena where realtime situations and challenges are waiting to be met and mastered.\r\n\r\n</p><br><br>', 'y'),
('netritva', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ol type="1"><li>The event is open to all irrespective of course, branch or year</li><br>\r\n<li>	This is an individual event</li><br>\r\n<li>All rounds are elimination rounds</li><br>\r\n<li>	Decision of organizers would be final and binding</li><br>\r\n<li>" Kindly mail your details (Name, Course, Year, Avishkar ID) at <b><a href="mailto:netritva.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">netritva.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b> "</li><br>\r\n</ol><br>', 'y'),
('sambang', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><h4 align="center">Be the advertising Avant-Grade.</h4><br><br>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:10px" src="events/sam_bang.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="image is loading"></img>Advertising has been a part of social setup since Adam. What has changed is its forms and presentation. <br><br>\r\nEgyptians, greeks and ancient romans used papyrus to make sales messages and wall posters. Wall and rock manifestations of ancient times are present to this day in many parts of Asia, Africa and South America. In 17th century, ads started to appear in weekly newspapers.<br><br>\r\nWith time, the ad forms and styling changed beyond recognition. Now successful ads are those that defy expectation and definition. An impressive ad cuts across various media be it print, visual or audio. Whose unexpected presence places a smile on our faces and a selling point in our collective conscious.<br><br>\r\n With Sambang we give you the chance to be a part of this advertising wave in which you have to advertise anything and everything under the sun. We give you the weirdest of products and you have to come up with the most exciting and innovative advertising strategies. <br><br>\r\nAnd, keep in mind even though its an idea that sets an ad apart from its peers, but, its the execution that takes it into realms of greatness. We recognize those who sweat the details coz its the details that make ads shine.<br><br>\r\n<br><br></p>', 'y'),
('sambang', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul><li>A team can consist of maximum two members.\r\n<br><br></li><li>All abstracts have to be submitted via mail to <b><a href="mailto:sambang.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">sambang.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b>.\r\n<br><br></li><li>The deadline for the submission of abstracts is September 20\r\n, 2011.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Innovation and thinking out of the box shall fetch you more marks. Humor and wit is thoroughly appreciated.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Obscenity is highly discouraged and will lead to instant disqualification.\r\n<br><br></li><li>The decision of the Judges and Event Coordinators will be final and binding.<br><br></li></ul>\r\n', 'y'),
('fina-delphia', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><h4><center> Feel the Rhythm of flickering market...</center></h4><br><br>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:10px" src="events/fina_delphia.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="image is loading..."></img>\r\n"One of the funny things about the stock market is that every time one person buys, another sells, and both think they are astute":William Feather.\r\n<br><br>\r\nFor all the Warren Buffet and Vikram Pandit fanatics envisaging colossal yields from their investments, take a crack at the financial province of Fina-Delphia, the metropolis which sports with capital and multiplies its wealth. Fina-Delphia provides you with a large horizon of investment options, but its precarious intricacies challenge every morsel of your financial returns till you engage the most prudent asset trade off and truly multiply your capital.</p><br><br>', 'y'),
('fina-delphia', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br><ul><li>Final Years can participate only in the first round (virtual trading) of the event but they will\r\nnot qualify for next round.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The trading starts on 7th September, 2011 and ends on 22th September, 2011.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>On the basis of NET PROFIT/LOSS from START on 22th September, 2011 (after closing\r\nof stock market) participants will qualify for next round.<br><br></li><li>\r\nThe 2nd round will be a written test, we would test your awareness of the share market.<br><br></li><li>\r\nThe 3rd round will be a share market Quiz.<br><br></li></ul>\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
('strategist', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4><center>"If Strategy without tactics is the slowest route to victory, Tactics without strategy is the noise before defeat":--Sun Tzu</center>	</h4><br><br> \r\n                             \r\n\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:10px" src="events/strategist.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="image is loading"></img>\r\nThe business world is filled with wars with relentless competition and ambiguous strategies. Strategy is about choice. The heart of a company''s strategy is what it chooses to do and not do. The quality of the thinking that goes into such choices is a key driver of the quality and success of a company''s strategy.<b> "Strategist-Quest for the Invincible Strategy"</b> is the demand for that prodigious skill and ingenuity which discerns the vanguard from the herd, the victor from the vanquished. So, gear up for the absolute test of your strategic acumen and knowledge to ignite the quest for the invincible strategy.<br><br>	\r\n<br><br>	\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('strategist', 3, 'Rules', '<br /><br /><ol type="1"><li>	There should be a team of three members.</li><br />\r\n	<li>Participants can team up with students of any branch and any year.</li><br>\r\n	<li>The first round will be online while the next round will be conducted at the college campus during Avishkar.</li></ol><br /><br />\r\n', 'y'),
('breakthrough', 5, 'FAQ', '<br><br>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 1.</td><td>Who can participate?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Any student from any college or university in India or abroad can participate.</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 2.</td><td>Can I copy some of the sentences directly from other papers or websites (say wikipedia) ?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>No.</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 3.</td><td>Where can I get more information regarding the event?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Send any queries regarding the event to <b><a href="mailto:breakthrough.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">breakthrough.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b> with subject as "QUERRY".</td></tr></table><br/><br/>', 'y'),
