('treasure_hunt', 2, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul><li>A team can have at most 2 members each having a valid Avishkar 2011 userid.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Teams also need to register on the Treasure Hunt portal which will be online soon<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The clues and hints will be available all throughout the website portal of Treasure Hunt. You are expected to explore the entire webpage including url changes.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Using any kind of unfair means including posting of answers in the forum or any hacking attempt will lead to immediate disqualification.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>At each level, you will be awarded a score based on the difficulty of question. The winner will be the team with highest score at the end or whoever hits the Treasure first.<br></li></ul>\r\n', 'y'),
('operaomnia', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center"><i>\r\n"The meeting point and fulcrum of this mighty axis between deep heaven and deep earth lies in human mind itself"</h4><br/><br/></i></br>\r\n<p align="justify" ><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/operaomnia.jpg" width="50%" align="left"  alt="operaomnia"></img>\r\nBored of thinking in a rectilinear fashion?<br/><br/> \r\nWant your mind to think in all dimensions?<br/><br/>\r\nHere is an event for you where you would be required to solve some simple yet out of the box puzzles which will be testing your analytical and mathematical skills.<br/><br/>\r\nThe event has no similitude to theoritical knowledge, which makes it one of the events with maximum participation. So, psych up to unravel the mysteries of some simple but unpredictable problems. \r\n<br/><br/><br><br>\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('operaomnia', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<ul><li>\r\nA team of maximum 2 persons can register for the event. The members of a team need \r\nnot belong to the same year and branch.<br><br></li><li>\r\nCoordinators reserve the right to disqualify any team found indulging in misbehavior.<br><br></li><li>\r\nThe decision of the Event Coordinators will be final and binding.<br><br></li></ul><br>\r\n', 'y');
INSERT INTO `tabs` (`id`, `tab_no`, `name`, `description`, `display`) VALUES
('sphinx', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center"><i>\r\n"Upholding the amaranthine quest of combating the puzzles"\r\n</h4><br/><br/></i></br>\r\n<p align="justify" ><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/sphinx.png" width="50%" align="left"  alt="sphinx"></img>\r\n"Puzzles are like songs - A good puzzle can give you all the pleasure of being duped \r\nthat a mystery story can. It has surface innocence, surprise, the revelation of a \r\nconcealed meaning, and the catharsis of solution." - Stephen Sondheim<br><br>\r\nThis event will delve you deep into the world of unique puzzles which will not only \r\nmesmerize you but will force you to push yourselves extra hard away from your \r\ncomfort zone where only your analytical skills can rescue you. <br><br>\r\nSo, be prepared to enter into deadly and virtually impenetrable "Chakravyuha" of  \r\n"SPHINX 2k11"  and get spellbound by the magic of puzzles.\r\n<br><br><br><br>\r\n</p><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('sphinx', 3, 'Rules', '\r\n<br><br>\r\n<ol><li>\r\nThe team may consist of at most 2 members.\r\n<br><br></li><li>The teams must adhere to the spirit of healthy competition and should not  \r\nindulge in practices like exchanging answers.\r\n<br><br></li><li>If in case, the coordinators feel that any team is involved in cheating, they \r\nhave full right to disqualify the team.\r\n<br><br></li><li>The decision of coordinators should be final and binding.<br><br></li></ol><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('mind_maze', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center"><i>\r\n"Re exploring Darwinism, only the fittest will survive"</h4><br/><h4 align="center"><a href="./mindmaze/">http://avishkar.in/mindmaze</a></h4><br/></i>\r\n</br><p align="justify" ><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/mindmaze.jpg" width="250px" align="left"  alt="mindmaze"></img>\r\nFlex your mental muscles.<br/><br/>\r\nIs your brain feeling underutilized? Not enough mental challenge in your day job?<br/><br/>\r\nWe can fix that.<br/><br/>\r\nMap the outer limits of your intellectual acuity and compete with the nation''s most logical minds\r\n<br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('chem_perfecto', 1, 'Introduction', '<br/><br/><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:60px" src="events/chem_perfecto.jpg" width="35%" align="left" alt="chem_perfecto"></img><p align="justify" >Intelligent,Smart,Professional. An excellent manager of time and a flawless knowledge of Chemical Engineering.. If this sounds someone like you, then Chem Perfecto is the event for you. Rather than a technical geek, the aim should be to develop a person who can survive the most hectic situation without any sign of break off or fatigue.<br/><br/>\r\nChem Perfecto, a unique masterpiece, proves to the world how good you are at "Real Engineering" and makes you stand apart from all others..<br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/></p>', 'y'),
('verte_globo', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">"I''m not an environmentalist.  I''m an Earth warrior." -Darryl Cherney</h4><br/><br/><br/><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:60px" src="events/verte_globo.jpg" width="50%" align="left" alt="verte_globo"></img><p align="justify" >\r\nIf you are an avid lover of nature and have in you the wits to recuperate the environment by bringing a change in present industrial set-up , Verte Globo is the event for you. With your idiosyncratic innovations and application of engineering skills remove the flaws of technology- in- use so to create a properous and greener earth.<br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('verte_globo', 2, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<ul><li>All participants must register themselves at <a href="mailto:verteglobo.rasayans2k11@gmail.com"><b>verteglobo.rasayans2k11@gmail.com</b> </a> by sending a mail containing Team name, name of the participants and contact details.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>No branch restriction for participation in this event.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The Event will consist of 2 rounds.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>There will be eliminations after 1st round.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>First round will be a written round in which there will be general questions related to Environment.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Second round will consist of questions on practical problems to which remedies must be provided by participants.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Decision of coordinators will be final and binding.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>For any queries, write to us at <a href="mailto:verteglobo.rasayans2k11@gmail.com"><b>verteglobo.rasayans2k11@gmail.com</b> </a> <br><br></li>\r\n</b>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br><br>', 'y'),
('chem_perfecto', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br><ul><li>All participants must register themselves at <b><a href="mailto:chemperfecto.rasayans2k11@gmail.com">chemperfecto.rasayans2k11@gmail.com</a></b> by sending a mail containing Team name, name of the participants and contact details.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Every Student of Chemical Engineering branch is eligible to participate in this event.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The Event will consist of 3 rounds.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>There will be eliminations after every round.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>First round will be a written round in which there will be 2 separate papers of Technical and Aptitude.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Written exam will be totally objective type.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>2nd round will be Group Discussion round.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>3rd and final round will be the Interview round. Technical and HR interviews will be taken separately.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>For any queries, write to us at <b><a href="mailto:chemperfecto.rasayans2k11@gmail.com">chemperfecto.rasayans2k11@gmail.com</a></b><br><br></li></ul>\r\n<br><br>', 'y'),
('contraption', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br><ul>\r\n  <li>The participants are supposed to solve the problem statements using maximum number of energy conversions.</li>\r\n<li>  All participants should submit an abstract to<!-- <a href="contraption.mechrocosm2k11@gmail.com">contraption.mechrocosm2k11@gmail.com</a>--> any of coordinators email.\r\n  <ul> <b>Abstract Details: </b><br />\r\n  Abstract should contain the followings: <br />\r\n  <li>Explanation for each and every step.</li>\r\n  <li>Total no of steps.</li>\r\n  <li>No of energy conversions.</li>\r\n  <li>If required, Sketches, Flowcharts to explain any step.</li>\r\n  <li>Mechanism, motivation and Cost of Setup/Construction.</li></ul></li>\r\n  <li>In-house participants are also required to submit the hard copy of abstract few days before event.</li>\r\n<li>Selected teams will have to display their working solution on event date and venue. Their performance will be judged by Faculty members.</li> <br />\r\n', 'y'),
('code_of_the_day', 5, 'Results', '<br><br><center><a href="./downloads/cod_result.pdf" target="_blank">Code of the Day Scoreboard</a><br><br>', 'y'),
('contraption', 3, 'Event Details', '<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Energy Conversion is change of energy from one form to another form.</li>\r\n<li>If the energy in the previous step is not used to drive the succeeding energy conversions directly, it would create a discontinuity in the circuit and thus would be considered as a link.<br/>\r\ne.g.: Light falling on a LDR activating an electrical circuit is considered as a link as no direct conversion from light to electricity is involved.\r\n</li>\r\n<li> Energy conversion from A to B is different from energy conversion B to A.</li></ul><br/>\r\n<h3>Energy Classification:</h3>\r\n<ul><li>The forms of energies considered are electrical, mechanical, wind, tidal, chemical, thermal, sound, and light.</li>\r\n<li>Only two forms of mechanical energy will be considered, i.e., potential Energy, kinetic Energy.</li>\r\n<li>Rotational Energy comes under Kinetic Energy.</li>\r\n<li>Wind Energy is different from kinetic energy and other forms of mechanical energy.</li></ul><br/>\r\n<h3>Scoring Patterns: </h3>\r\n<ul><li>Each team will be given maximum three attempts.</li>\r\n<li>Every first energy conversion A to B will be awarded certain points.</li>\r\n<li> Each repeated energy conversion A to B will be awarded points.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Points will be also awarded for using parallel energy conversions.\r\n</li>\r\n<li> Points will be awarded on Number of steps, Number of energy conversion,Motivation and mechanism.</li> \r\n<li>A person shall not be the member of more than one team.\r\n</li>\r\n<li> Teams making more than one model will be given extra credits and appreciation.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Teams cannot use any pre built machinery available in market.\r\n</li>\r\n<li> Maximum two human interventions will be allowed.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>At the Maximum two trials will be allowed.\r\n</li></ul><br><br>', 'y'),
('bio_vision', 2, 'Event Format', '<br /><br /><b>\r\n1.	Preliminary Round</b><br /><br />\r\n This round shall comprise of a live treasure hunt in the Biotechnology laboratory wherein you will be provided with certain clues to direct you to various instruments and chemicals.\r\nThis will be an elimination round.<br /><br />\r\n\r\n<b>2.	Second Round</b>\r\n<br /><br />You will be required to perform an on the spot allotted experiment related to any one of the fields- Microbiology, Cellular and Molecular biology, Instrumentation and Genetic Engineering.<br /><br />\r\n', 'y'),
('webster', 5, 'FAQS', '<br>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 1.</td><td>I am not from stream CS/IT. Can I take part?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>People from all streams and disciplines can take part.\r\n\r\n </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 2.</td><td >What technical knowledge should I have to be a part of Webster ? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:<br><br><br><br></td><td>The basic requirements of Webster are elementary knowledge of Website Designing which includes HTML/CSS, some server side scripting languages like PHP/JSP and basic implementation of Databases. You can readily refer to the tutorials available on the Internet.\r\n</td></tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 3.</td><td >What if I cannot fulfill all the objectives mentioned?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:<br></td><td>It is not a problem since there are marks for all aspects of your website.\r\n\r\n \r\n</td></tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 4.</td><td >Where am I supposed to host my site for the presentation?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:<br></td><td>You will be provided with a webserver to host your website . So, you need to be clear about the basics of hosting a website \r\n \r\n</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 5.</td><td >I do not have a laptop to host my website?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:<br></td><td>We will be giving a webserver to host your website so , you can also host your website from there too .\r\n</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 6.</td><td >I am MCA first year student from MNNIT can I attempt problem statement 1?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:<br></td><td>Yes , you can but the problem statement 1 is for the first year B.tech. students so they will have an advantage over you . Also if you are trying to attempt problem statement 1 , you will have to make your website dynamic and also have to make it for users greater than 5.Considering that you are making it for a group of people. \r\n \r\n</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 7.</td><td >I am a first year from MNNIT can I attempt the other problems?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:<br></td><td>Yes,you can attempt the other problems too and if you attempt them you will be given some advantage for that.\r\n \r\n</td></tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</table><br/><br/>\r\n', 'y'),
