('code of the day', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br><ol type="1">\r\n<li>This event will be of 10 days.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>It will start on 11th September,2011.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>There will be three levels- level A, level B and level C.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Level A will contain 3 questions, level B contains 4 questions and level C contains 3 questions.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Difficulty level of questions will increase according to the level.<br><br></li>\r\n</ol><br>\r\n\r\n<b><u>FAQ</u></b>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 1.</td>\r\n<td>  What does correct solution means?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> Correct solution means that<ul><li>It should give correct output in the specified format.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>It should give correct output within the time limit specified for the problem<br><br></li></ul></td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 2.</td><td> Is there any extra weight-age to efficient solution?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> No. However, the solution must be within the time limits specified for the problem.</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 3.</td><td>What is Presentation Error?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>The format of your answer is not correct. Only the required data, as shown in the sample test case has to be printed.\r\n     For instance, printing "YES" instead of "Yes" will give you Presentation Error.\r\n     If you get this error, then it doesn''t mean that your logic for the problem is correct.</td></tr> \r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 4.</td><td> Where can I get more information about the event?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>For further queries you can mail us at <b><a href="mailto:codeo