('iopc', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br><ol type="1"><li>No elimination round. Everyone can participate.</li><br>\r\n<li>Event is of  6 hours duration.</li><br>\r\n<li>Event will have 6 problems all with varying Time Limit.</li><br>\r\n<li>Problem statements would be released during the event.</li><br>\r\n<li>Problem format:<br> \r\nFor each problem you will have to submit a code that will take input from standard input, process that input according to the problem statement and then output in on standard output.</li><br>\r\n<li>	You can submit a problem more than once, there is no penalty for wrong submissions.</li><br>\r\n<li>	Each Problem is of 1 marks, in case of tie sum total of the time taken to submit each problem is taken into consideration.</li><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ol>', 'y'),
('iopc', 5, 'FAQS', '<br>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 1.</td><td> What is time limit? And how does it work?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:<br><br><br><br></td><td>You will receive input from stdin, and your code should read, process and print the output (to stdout) within the specified time limit. If input has multiple test cases, then remember that the time limit is not for a single test case. All test cases should execute within  the specified time limit.\r\n </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 2.</td><td >Why am I getting compilation errors? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:<br><br><br><br><br><br><br></td><td>Check if the code compiles without any error on your machine. Always make sure you do not use anything that is not a standard feature of the language.\r\n Some common reasons for compilation error in C/C++, Java:<br><br>\r\n \r\n For C/C++ make sure you are using a gcc/g++ compiler. Do not use conio.h. Do not use headers that are not standard headers.\r\nIn Java, make sure you are not using any packages. Make sure the class containing "Main" is public.\r\n\r\n \r\n</td></tr>\r\n\r\n</table><br/><br/>\r\n', 'y'),
