('scrapheap', 3, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Open to all branches from all courses.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Team of three (all the members should be from the same year and at least one from Mechanical Engineering Department).<br><br></li>\r\n<li>The first two rounds are elimination round.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>There should be scientific thesis to support your logic.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>All the team members must be present during the finals.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>''Scrapheap'' organizing team reserves the right to eliminate the participants in case of any misconduct.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>In case of any discrepancy the decision of the judges will be final.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Outside participants will be given direct entry to the <b>second</b> round but they have to inform beforehand.<br><br></li></ul>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Judging Parameters:</b><br><br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Creativity & Innovativeness<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Feasibility <br><br></li>\r\n<li>Material & Cost effectiveness<br><br></li>\r\n<li>There will be added incentive for first year students as we do not check your technical ability so they can directly compete with second and third year students.<br><br></li></ul><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Those who wish to participate are required to send us their details which should have:</b><br><br>\r\n<ol type="1">\r\n<li>College Name<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Team name<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Name of participants viz-a-viz branch & Reg. No.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Contact information which should include email id & mobile number of all.<br><br></li></ol><br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\nFeel free to contact any of the co-coordinators for any queries regarding this event<br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
