('sparks', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br>\r\nSparks is a Paper Presentation contest. Papers to be presented should be based on original work/idea and directed to or based on some basic electrical or electronics phenomena. The papers would be evaluated in three rounds.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Round1 :</b><br><br>\r\n<b>Abstract submission -</b> Participants would mail a brief overview of their idea or work in about 200 words detailing the scope of their work, the basic principles involved, analytical treatment of the matter and results. The papers must be sent in IEEE Single Column Format (see Sample Formats) in either .doc or .pdf file.<br><br>\r\n<b>Round 2 :</b><br><br>\r\n<b>Paper submission - </b>Selected participants must prepare a detailed paper incorporating the field of the application, background of the innovation, circuit or model of the application design, analytical and mathematical treatment, simulations and results along with scope for improvements, with special emphasis on own contribution in a lucid and elaborative paper, in IEEE Double Column Standard Format (see Sample Formats) in either .doc or .pdf file.<br><br>\r\n<b>Round 3 :</b><br><br>\r\nSelected participants would be required to give a presentation in Power point or Macromedia Flash, detailing their work, innovation, findings and results, before an esteemed panel of judges, in about 9+1 minutes. The presentation would be followed by questions from the panel of judges and the audience.<br><br>\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
