('vortex', 2, 'Event Format', '<Br /><Br />Vortex is a fluid mechanics event. Students have to prepare a rocket utilizing water for its propulsion. All the teams participating will face the following two rounds:<br /><br />\r\n	\r\n<strong>ROUND 1- DESIGN SUBMISSION:</strong><br /><br /><ol type="1">\r\n\r\n<li>	All the participating teams have to submit the design of their rocket and all its details (Process, material, range, time of flight, diagram etc.)</li><br />\r\n<li> The details must be mailed to vortex2k11@gmail.com</li><br />\r\n<li>Last date for submission of the designs is <b>20 SEPTEMBER 2011</b>.</li><br />\r\n<li>Send the designs to vortex2k11@gmail.com in a DOC /DOCX /PDF file.</li><br />\r\n\r\n\r\n    <br /></ol><strong>ROUND 2- PROPULSION TEST:</strong><br />\r\n<br>\r\n<ol type="1"><li>In this round, the range and time of flight of the rocket will be tested.</li><br />\r\n<li>Points will be awarded as per the equation given below<br />     \r\n Points = (3 x Range) + (5 x Time).</li><br /></ol>\r\n', 'y'),
