('crossover', 4, 'Abstract Submission', '<br><br><b><center>CROSSOVER :-National Bridge Design \r\nChallenge Competition </center></b><br><br>\r\n \r\n<center><b>Abstract Submission  </b></center><br><br>\r\n<b>In order to qualify for the event, you are required to submit your bridge design either \r\nthrough PDF file or on drawing sheet(manually). The abstract should specify the name, \r\nbranch, and college''s name of each team member. The quality of your design and analysis \r\nwill decide your eligibility for the event. Please make note of the following key points to be \r\ncovered in your submission: </b><br><br>\r\n<ul><li>\r\nYou must make a neat <b>sketch</b> of the frontal frame and the plan view of the deck and the roof \r\nof the bridge, with <b>proper dimensioning</b>. It should also contain the geometry of the section \r\nof the members (e.g. mention that you are making a particular member using 7 spaghetti \r\nsticks). A Three-dimensional sketch is also acceptable, provided the geometry of the design is \r\nclearly visible. <br><br></li><li>\r\nYou must do the <b>structural analysis of the frontal frame</b> for the critical load. If you are \r\nusing some software for the same, then mention the type of analysis done by that software . \r\n<br><br></li><li>Highlight the members differently for tensile and compressive stress. \r\n<br><br></li><li>Mention the advantages gained by using your design and other special features of the design, \r\nif you can. \r\n<br><br></li><li>Calculate the theoretical maximum load that can be taken by your bridge. Also explain \r\nwhether the bridge would be able to take up that much load practically. How much do you \r\nexpect it to withstand in the contest until failure? <br><br></li></ul><br><br><br>\r\nThe last date for the submission of abstract is <b>18 september 2011</b>.<br><br> Please mail all the entries to      \r\n<b><a href="mailto:crossover2k11@gmail.com"> crossover2k11@gmail.com </a></b> <br><br>\r\n \r\n<b>NOTE :</b>You are not allowed to change your bridge design after submission, under \r\nany circumstances. You will have to abide by your submitted design while making \r\nthe bridge. Any changes found in the final structure of the bridge are liable to your \r\ndisqualification from the contest. So, make sure you rack your brains hard and come \r\nup with an exciting one! <br><br>\r\n \r\n<i>If you want to change your design then please resubmit your design to \r\n<b><a href="mailto:crossover2k11@gmail.com"> crossover2k11@gmail.com </a></b>  ,before the submission deadline </i><br><br>\r\n \r\n ', 'y'),
('softbuild', 2, 'Event Format', '<br /><br /><b>Soft Build is an event in which the participating teams will have to develop computer programmes for solving real life Civil Engineering Problems</b><br /><br>\r\n<strong>ROUND 1- ELIMINATION ROUND :</strong><br /><br>\r\nThis will consist of online submission of the solution to the problems, before the main event by the participating teams.<br><br>\r\nCoding must be done in C, C++or JAVA.<br><br>\r\nSoftware packages allowed are STAAD pro and SAP only. <br><br>\r\nThe selection criteria will be the logic and execution time for the codes and the accuracy of solutions in STAAD Pro, SAP.<br /><br /><br>\r\n<strong>ROUND 2- FINAL ROUND :</strong><br /><br>\r\nFinal round for the event will be held on the AVISHKAR day.<br><br>\r\nThis will be an on the spot coding and computer aided problem solving round.<br><br>\r\nDuration of the test will be 150 mins.\r\n<br /><br />', 'y'),
