('udaan', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br><h4 align="center">Udaan 2</h4><br><br>\r\n<p align="justify"><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="./events/udaan.jpg" width="90%" align="left" alt="Image is loading...please wait "></img>After huge success of this event in avishkar 2010, this time also its back, to make you feel the rush\r\nof adrenalin. Aeromodelling was always the best adventure sport anyone can do. Although its time\r\ntaking but the pleasure you get when you fly your own hand built plane is priceless. The problem\r\nstatement is made simpler this year but we have also added more fun into it.\r\n<br></p>\r\n<b>Problem Statement:</b><br><br>\r\n\r\nDesign a free flight hand launch glider and tune it for maximum range and time of flight.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Rules:</b><br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Wingspan should be of maximum 500mm.<br><br></li><li>\r\nYou cannot use readymade models, but you can use pre-cut kits.\r\n<br><br></li><li>The point system will be based on Range and Time of flight only.\r\n<br><br></li><li>In case of tie, other factors like design etc can be taken into consideration.\r\n<br><br></li><li>You cannot use launching mechanism. Only hand launch is allowed.\r\n<br><br></li><li>There is no team, participation will be on individual basis.<br><br></li></ul>', 'y'),
('fading_blue', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br>This event has following rounds:<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>ROUND 1: WRITTEN ROUND:</b><br><br>\r\nThis will consist of objective questions which will be related to water resources, water pollution and its contamination and general awareness about the same. Basic knowledge of environmental engineering is required.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>ROUND 2: PHOTO PRESENTATION ROUND:</b><br><br>\r\n<ul><li>All the shortlisted candidates from the written examination will be eligible for this round.<br><br></li><li>\r\nIt will consist of survey of an area(of their own choice)in which the students have to click photographs related to water contamination issues and make a Power Point Presentation using those pics.\r\n<br><br></li><li>Students can increase their area of data collection as per their accord to nearby areas. \r\n<br><br></li><li>The presentation should be concluded with logical, practical and reliable solutions to the problems. However, if required, students can represent some additional models to describe their idea more clearly.<br><br></li></ul>\r\n', 'y'),
