('sphinx', 5, 'FAQ', '<br><br>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 1.</td><td>Who can participate?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Any student from any college or university in India or abroad can participate.</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 2.</td><td >What is the size of each team?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Each team can have maximum of 2 participants</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Q 3.</td>\r\n<td >Where can I get more information regarding this event? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>You can contact the event coordinators or drop an email to <br>\r\n  <b><a href="mailto:sphinx.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">sphinx.avishkar2k11@gmail.com </a></b> with subject as ''QUERY''</td></tr>\r\n\r\n</table><br/><br/>\r\n', 'y'),
('treasure_hunt', 3, 'Contacts', '<br><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<table><tr height="30px">\r\n  <td width="300px">    Manish Pandey </td><td width="300px">+91-9451071769</td><td width="300px">manishpandeymp@gmail.com</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="30px">\r\n  <td width="300px">\r\nLakhan Arya</td><td width="300px">+91-9457433725</td><td width="300px">lakhan.arya@gmail.com</td></tr>\r\n</table>\r\n', 'y'),
('dota', 1, 'Introduction', '<h4 align="center">"You wanna get the undead? I''ll tell you how to get the undead. One of their men pulls a knife, your man pulls a gun, they send your man to the hospital, you send their man to the morgue. Thats how you get the undead." - LORD OF OLYMPIA\r\n</h4><br/><br/></br>\r\n<p align="justify" ><img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/dota.jpg" width="50%" align="left"  alt="dota"></img>\r\nDefense Of The Ancients the ultimate RTS (Real Time strategy) with RPG (Role Playing Game) combat and an international scope. The scenario was featured by Computer Gaming World in a review of new maps and mods in Warcraft III. DOTA has become a feature at several worldwide tournaments, including Blizzard Entertainment''s BlizzCon and the Asian World Cyber Games, as well as the Cyberathlete Amateur and CyberEvolution leagues. In this Avishkar 2011, a new challenge awaits us all! A brilliant game with simple concept and complex strategy, with tactics and traps, with ambush and backstab... Let''s get the First Blood!!\r\n<br><br><br><br><br><br>\r\n</p>', 'y'),
('dota', 2, 'Rules', '<br><br>\r\n<b>Important RULES expected to be followed by all Dota players.</b><br><br>\r\n<ol><li><b>No Creep-jacking your allies: </b><br><br>Creep jacking your allies is when you see one of your allies creeping and you deliberatly go to the spot he is creeping at, and try to get the creep kill, or the last hit on the creep. <br><br></li>\r\n<li><b>No Kill Stealing: </b><br><br>Kill Stealing is similar to Creep jacking; you wait until one of your allies brings an enemy hero down to low health, and then you interfere, with the intent to get the hero kill for yourself. The action is referred to as a "KS." <br><br></li>\r\n<li><b>No Stealing items from a teammate still playing:</b><br><br>This is possible to do by picking up an item one of your allies has purposely dropped in order to purchase something else. An ally will never put down an item he doesn''t intend to use in the future, and picking up something that''s not yours is stealing. \r\n\r\n<br><br></li>\r\n<li><b>No petty/lame jokes intended for the purpose of annoying your teammates</b><br></li></ol>\r\n', 'y'),
('dota', 3, 'Game Settings', '<br><br>\r\n<b>The DOTA event will be held in two different formats:</b><br><br>\r\n<ol><li><b>1.	3 on 3 DOTA map</b><br><br>This will consist of 3 players each on both sides i.e., SENTINEL AND SCOURGE with 2 lanes. That is the say, only the mid and the bottom lanes. The team pushing through the enemy forces and destroying the WORLD TREE or the FROZEN THRONE will be considered the winner. <br><br></li>\r\n<li><b>2.	5 on 5 DOTA map</b><br><br>This will consist of the finals and pre-finals were the match will be between 5 players each from the SENTINEL and SCOURGE. All the lanes will be open for this map.<br><br></li></ol>\r\n<b>Note: </b>Every team has to decide their own captain.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>The game mode that will be followed is </b><br><br>\r\n<ul><li><b>Primary modes: </b><br><br>\r\n<ul type="square"><li>cm (captains mode), <br><br></li>\r\n<li>cd (captains draft), <br><br></li>\r\n<li>cdnt or cdnb (for 3 on 3 match) <br><br></li></ul></li>\r\n<li><b>Secondary modes: </b><br><br>\r\n<ul type="square"><li>nt<br><br></li><li>nb<br><br></li></ul></li></ul>\r\n<b>Map version: DOTA -6 .72f</b><br><br>\r\nPlayers can use their own warkeys.<br><br>\r\nUsing of unauthorised commands and scripts will result in disqualification of the players or the team.<br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('biz_quizz', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br>The participating teams have to choose any one of the following products: <br><br>\r\n<ol type="1"><li>Fanta Apple. </li>\r\n<li> Woome (Social Networking site). </li>\r\n<li> TVS Jive </li>\r\n<li> Microsoft Kin Mobile.</li>\r\n<li> Parle Chox (Toffee).</li>\r\n</ol><br><br>\r\nThe plan should include the following: <br><br><ol type="1">\r\n<li> Reasons for failure. (Not exceeding 300 words) .</li>\r\n<li> Rationale behind the re-launch (not exceeding 400 words).</li> \r\n<li> STP Analysis (not exceeding 400 words).</li> \r\n<li> Marketing Mix (not exceeding 400 words).</li> \r\n<li> Financials (breakup of details of investment, not exceeding 1 page).</li>\r\n<br><br></ol>\r\nYOU SHOULD MAIL YOUR ABSTRACTS AT <a href="mailto:bizquizz.avishkar2k11@gmail.com "><b>bizquizz.avishkar2k11@gmail.com </b></a> <br> \r\n\r\nLast date for submission of abstracts is 15th September 2011by 12 midnight  .<br><br>\r\n \r\n<b>Guidelines: </b><br><br>\r\nThe plan should have a cover page that indicates: <br><br><ol type="1">\r\n<li> Name of the institute .</li>\r\n<li> Names of all team members (3 members per Group).</li>\r\n<li> E-mail addresses and telephone numbers of all team members.</li> \r\n<li> Chosen product and the company for which the executive summary has been prepared.</li> \r\n<li> Extra Appendices can be attached to explain financials or other data. </li>\r\n \r\n </ol><br><br>\r\n<b>On Campus: </b><br><ol type="1">\r\n<li> This round will be held at MNNIT Allahabad during Avishkar 2011.</li>\r\n<li> The short listed teams are required to present their solutions to a panel of judges.</li> \r\n<li> The participants will have to give their presentation in Macromedia Flash / Microsoft Power point. </li>\r\n<li> Movie Clippings or Recorded dialogues, Surveys can be used to support their ideas. </li>\r\n<li> The time for the presentation will be 11 minutes plus 1 minute to wind up. This will be followed by a question and answer session of 3 minutes duration. </li></ol>\r\n<br><br>', 'n'),
('strategist', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br>There will be 2 rounds:<br><br>\r\n<strong>First Round:</strong><br><br><ol type="1">\r\n\r\n<li>This will be an online round in which the teams will be provided with case studies dealing with strategic issues faced by business houses, corporate giants & other organizations.</li><br>\r\n<li>There will be three cases and teams can submit solutions to either of them.</li><br>\r\n<li>This is basically a screening round and only the shortlisted teams will move on to the next round.</li><br>\r\n<li>Please mail your solutions on the following email id: <a href="mailto:strategist.avishkar2k11@gmail.com"><b>strategist.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</b></a> on or before 19th September 2011.</li><br></ol><br>	\r\nRound 1 Case Studies<br><br>\r\n<a href="http://avishkar.in/events/strategist_case1.pdf"> <b>Download Case_study 1.pdf</b></a><br>\r\n<a href="http://avishkar.in/events/strategist_case2.pdf"> <b>Download Case_study 2.pdf</b></a><br>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://avishkar.in/events/strategist_case3.pdf"> <b>Download Case_study 3.pdf</b></a><br>\r\n\r\n<br><br><!--<ul type="disc">	\r\n<li>Case study 1</li>\r\n<li>	Case study 2</li>\r\n<li>Case study 3</li></ul>--><br><br>\r\n<strong>Second Round	</strong><br><br>\r\n\r\n<ul type="disc"><li>This is a "Negotiation Round".</li>\r\n<li>Teams will be paired up and a business problem will be forwarded to the two teams.</li>\r\n<li>The selected teams will be designated as certain business organisation teams where the team members have to assume roles of   Chief Financial Officer, Chief Executive Officer and Chief Marketing Officer among them.</li>\r\n<li>	A 10-15 minutes negotiation session should yield a certain MoU (Memorandum of Understanding) between the two business houses.</li>\r\n<li>After the negotiation session, there will be a questionnaire round between the teams and the judges.\r\n</li></ul><br><br>\r\n\r\nPlease mail your solutions and queries on the following email id:<a href="mailto:strategist.avishkar2k11@gmail.com"><b>strategist.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</b></a><br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('sambang', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br>The event will be conducted in three stages. All three are elimination rounds.<br><br>\r\n<ol><li><b>Abstract Submission:</b>  You''ll be given a choice of three hypothetical weird products and you need to choose one and develop a complete advertising strategy including descriptions of sales strategy, marketing strategy, description of ads you shall use in print as well as electronic media, USP of your product and anything else you wish to include.<br><br></li><li>\r\n<b>Written Test:</b>  This will be a pen paper test to check your knowledge of the advertising world. You might also be asked to sketch some print media ads or provide interesting taglines. Depending on the number of teams in this round there may or may not be an additional round wherein you shall be given a product and you''ll need to enact a television ad on the spot.<br><br></li><li><b> Presentation Round: </b>The teams selected for this round will each be given a different real life product and they will have to formulate a formal advertising strategy for it and present it in front of the judges as a powerpoint presentation. You will also be expected to come up with a print media ad/poster as well as  electronic media ads like a television clipping or a radio jingle for your product.\r\n<br><br></li></ol>', 'y'),
