('webster', 3, 'Problem Statement', '<br /><br />\r\nProblem Statement 1: <u><a href="./events/webster1.pdf" target="_blank">Express Yourself (Only for MNNIT B.Tech. 1st year students)</a></u><br /><br />\r\nProblem Statement 2: <u><a href="./events/webster2.pdf" target="_blank">Attendance Manager</a></u><br /><br />\r\nProblem Statement 3: <u><a href="./events/webster3.pdf" target="_blank">Secure Online Repository System</a></u><br /><br />\r\nProblem Statement 4: <u><a href="./events/webster4.pdf" target="_blank">Social Networking Website</a></u><br /><br />\r\nProblem Statement 5: <u><a href="./events/webster5.pdf" target="_blank">Multi-Purpose Online Examination Portal</a></u><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<p align="center">Download: <u><a href="./events/webster_abstract.doc" target="_blank">Abstract Submission Format</a></u></p>', 'y'),
('fifa', 5, 'Contacts', '<br><br>\r\n<table><tr height="40px">\r\n  <td width="400">Nitesh Srivastav</td>\r\n<td width="400">+91-7275260026</td><td width="400">nitesh.chs@gmail.com </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="40px">\r\n  <td width="400">Pankaj Kumar</td>\r\n<td width="400">+91-9792779080</td><td width="400">kumar.pankaj.2791@gmail.com </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="40px">\r\n  <td width="400">Akash Jain</td>\r\n<td width="400">+91-8004960615</td><td width="400">akashjain2012@gmail.com </td></tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<br><br>	', 'y'),
('clairvoyance', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br><b>1.	Preliminary Round</b><br><br>\r\nThe participant will have to submit an abstract of maximum 250 words stating an overview of your idea and the innovation involved. The abstract should be sent in .doc, .docx or .pdf format only.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>2.	Second Round</b><br><br>\r\nThe participants whose abstracts will be selected after the first round need to give a power point presentation presenting their idea and complete concept in front of the faculty members in the Department of Biotechnology. Clarity of concepts with least minimum cut-copy-paste work shall be appreciated.<br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
('clairvoyance', 4, 'FAQ', '<br><br>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 1.</td><td>If I am not from Biology background, am I fit for this event?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Yes, definitely! You just have to give an innovative idea or a solution to an existing problem. The idea doesn''t have to involve hardcore biology. It should just involve one or more techniques of Biotechnology.</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 2.</td><td>Will my idea be rejected if it''s not feasible?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>No. It won''t be rejected until it completely defies the basic scientific principles. But the ideas closer to reality and having practical applications would be given preference.</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 3.</td><td>What should my  presentation look like?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Presentations are  meant to test your ability to express your ideas. Your presentation should  comprise mainly of pictures, diagrams and statistical data. Use bullets and try  to make it less wordy. Avoid paragraphs please. All the information you are  using should be supported with proper references.</td></tr><tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n  <td width="50px">Q 4.</td><td>Where to start? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Visit the websites of major journals. For eg.  <b><a href="www.sciencedirect.com">www.sciencedirect.com,</a><a href="www.nature.com">www.nature.com</a></b>  etc. Narrow down your search and go through the work already done and the unsettled questions and propose a feasible solution to them.\r\n\r\n</td></tr><tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n  <td width="50px">Q 5.</td>\r\n  <td>What ideas have already been put forth in previous years?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>These are the idea on which work has been done:\r\n<br><br><ul><li>Bioelectronics\r\n<br><br></li><li>Biosensors\r\n<br><br></li><li>Bioremediation\r\n<br><br></li><li>Biomedical applications of micro-organisms\r\n<br><br></li><li>Industrial applications of plant products\r\n\r\n</li></ul>\r\n</td></tr>\r\n\r\n</table><br/><br/>\r\n', 'y'),
('cryptochrome', 2, 'Event Format', '<br /><br />It is an online treasure hunt related to the field of Biotechnology. <br /><br />\r\nClues shall be provided at each level. In case you answer correctly you move on to the next level else you remain at the same level. \r\nHints will be given from time to time on each question level, as well as on the blog <b><u><a href="http://cryptochrome-genesis2k11.blogspot.com">http://cryptochrome-genesis2k11.blogspot.com</a></u></b><br /><br />', 'y'),
('double_helix', 4, 'FAQ', '\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 1.</td><td>Can a team consist of participant from different colleges/institutes?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Yes but an MNNITian cannot form a team with any other college student.</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 2.</td><td>I am a 1st/ 2nd year student. Can I have a partner from any other year?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Yes</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 3.</td><td>How should I prepare for the quiz?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>The preliminary round (for MNNITians) will have very easy questions about biotechnology which  	we use in our daily life and basic technology. So just be updated. <br><br>\r\n         The second and third round consists of questions/puzzles from biotechnology(core). You may read the following topics for preparation for these rounds<br><br>\r\n         <ol><li>	Biochemistry  \r\n<br><br></li><li>Genetics \r\n<br><br></li><li>Immunology \r\n<br><br></li><li>Recombinant DNA technology  \r\n<br><br></li><li>Cell biology\r\n<br><br></li><li>Bioprocess engineering  \r\n<br><br></li><li>Microbiology </li></ol>\r\n\r\n</td></tr><tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 4.</td><td>Is differential marking applicable in 1st round if a team consist of a member from two different years ?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Yes but the team will be ranked according to the senior member.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</td></tr><tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 5.</td><td>Where can I get more information about the event?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Mail your queries regarding the event to <b><a href="mailto:genesis.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">genesis.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b> or any of cordinator''s mail ID.\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 6.</td><td>This event is clashing with one of my other event. What should I do?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Contact the coordinators of both the events.\r\n</td></tr>\r\n\r\n</table><br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
('paladin', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br>Paladin shall consist of 3 rounds:<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>1.	Preliminary round</b><br><br>\r\nThis shall be a written test that shall check your aptitude as well as basic knowledge of C. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>2.	Second Round</b><br><br>\r\nThis shall comprise of group discussion which shall give you an idea of the various rules that should be followed during a GD. Your leadership skills and coordination with a team shall be tested here. The panels will be decided by the coordinators. The participants are required to be in formals for the GD.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>3.	Last Round</b><br><br>\r\nThis is an interview round. Both tech and HR interviews shall be taken. All participants should be in formals. For the first year students reaching to this round, no tech interview shall be taken, they will have to appear only for the HR interview.<br><br>\r\n', 'y');
INSERT INTO `tabs` (`id`, `tab_no`, `name`, `description`, `display`) VALUES
('adrenaline_rush', 2, 'Event Format', '<br><br>This event comprises of two rounds:<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>1.	Preliminary round</b><br><br>\r\nIt will comprise of an abstract submission wherein you will be provided with a set of problems. Teams will submit their solutions within the set time limit. You can google for the answers. It is an elimination round. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>2.	Second Round</b><br><br>\r\nThis shall be an on-the-spot round. For this, you need to have some basic knowledge in the field of biotechnology. You will be provided a problem and you will be required to submit a solution to it.<br><br>', 'y'),
('adrenaline_rush', 5, 'FAQ', '<br><br>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 1.</td><td> On  what basis our abstract will be judged? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> You  will be marked on the basis of,  <br>\r\n   1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Creativity  and innovation<br>\r\n    2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Content<br>\r\n    3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Feasibility  of the idea<br>\r\n    4)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Approach  to the problem<br>\r\n  5)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If  the process is industrial then it should be economic </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 2.</td>\r\n<td>Which  book to be brought for ''Open Book'' round?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> Genetics,  Bioprocess and plant design, Biochemistry etc (first years may contact final  years for these books) </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 3.</td>\r\n<td>How  to prepare?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> Just  keep yourself updated with the latest news in the field of biotechnology. Core  biotech will not be asked. </td></tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 4.</td>\r\n<td> What  are the chances of winning for first years? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> There  will be differential marking for all 1st 2nd and 3rd  years, so there are equal opportunities for all years to win. </td></tr>\r\n\r\n\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 5.</td>\r\n<td>  Will marks of ''Open Google'' round be added in ''Open Book'' round?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> Yes  the final result will be decided on the basis of performance in both the  rounds.&nbsp; </td></tr>\r\n\r\n</table><br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
('robotics_workshop', 1, 'Introduction', '<br><br>\r\n<h4 align="center">ROBOTICS WORKSHOP "iSensoBotz Elex"  successfully completed with over\r\n200 participants</h4><br><br>\r\n"iSENSOBOTZ Elex -  experiencing science and technology through fun way of  robotics"  is a workshop especially conducted to build autonomous robot  without using Microcontroller. <br><br>\r\nParticipants will be able to apply the concepts  which were studied in the 1st  and 2nd  year of \r\nEngineering. It''s a fun way to building autonomous robot, applying basic concepts. <br><br>\r\n<b> \r\nThis workshop is for young technical minds and robotics enthusiasts of all  disciplines from diploma Institutes to Engineering Colleges of all the branches  like Electronics, Telecommunication, Mechanical, Computer Science etc.  iSENSOBOTZ Elex workshop is specially designed to simplify the journey of autonomous robots for the students. It includes the basics of Electronics, Mechanics, IT, etc. \r\n</b><br><br>\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/robotics_workshop.png" width="92%" align="left" alt="image is loading..."></img>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Who should attend? </b><br><br>\r\n<ul><li>B.E/B.Tech students of following branches \r\nElectronics, Telecommunication, Computer science, Information technology, \r\nMechanical, Instrumentation <br><br></li>	\r\n<li>Diploma engineering student of following branches \r\nElectronics, Telecommunication, Computer Science, Information technology, \r\nmechanical, instrumentation \r\n<br><br></li></ul>\r\n\r\n<b>What would you learn? </b><br><br>\r\n<ul><li>Basic electronic components and their working principle <br><br></li>	\r\n<li>\r\nBasics of Robotics <br><br></li>	\r\n<li>\r\nThe electronics behind robots \r\n<br><br></li>	\r\n<li>The mechanism behind the robots \r\n<br><br></li>	\r\n<li>Making your own automated robot with an electronic brain and electromechanical muscles\r\n<br><br></li>	\r\n<li>Inter facing mobile phone with your robot \r\n<br><br></li>	\r\n<li>Use of sound sensor and optical sensor and timer <br><br></li>	\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<b>Robots can be made using this kit  </b><br><br>\r\n\r\n<ol><li>IR wireless controlled robot \r\n<br><br></li><li>Line follower robot \r\n<br><br></li><li>Obstacle avoider robot \r\n<br><br></li><li>Obstacle follower robot \r\n<br><br></li><li>Photo phobic robot \r\n<br><br></li><li>Photo tropic robot \r\n<br><br></li><li>Wall follower robot \r\n<br><br></li><li>Firefighter robot \r\n<br><br></li><li>Mobile phone controlled robot \r\n<br><br></li><li>Sound controlled robot \r\n<br><br></li><li>Time controlled robot</li></ol>\r\n<img style=" border-bottom-style:solid;border-right-style:solid;border-left-style:solid; border-color:transparent; border-width:8px; border-bottom-width:20px" src="events/robotics_workshop1.png" width="92%" alt="image is loading..."></img>\r\n<br><br>', 'y'),
('robotics_workshop', 2, 'Information', '<p align="center">\r\n    <b><u><a target="_blank" href="./events/robotics_workshop.pdf">Download Registration Form</a></u></b>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Duration</b><br><br>\r\n2 days each day 8 hour on 17th and 18th September at MNNIT Allahabad. <br><br>\r\n<b>Timings</b><br><br>\r\n 9:00 AM to 6:00 PM<br><br>\r\n<b>Charges & Participation </b><br><br>\r\nParticipation Charges: Rs 1250 per participant<br><br>\r\nThe charges include: <br><br>\r\n<ul><li>Training fee of the 2 day workshop \r\n<br><br></li><li>Takeaway iSENSOBOZ Elex Training kit \r\n<br><br></li><li>Information cd (Fully loaded with notes, related software required for \r\n<br><br></li><li>iSENSOBOTZ Elex & videos of various competitions like ROBOCON,\r\n<br><br></li><li>ROBOWARS, Innovative Robots etc)\r\n<br><br></li><li>Individual participation certificate<br><br></li></ul>\r\n\r\n<b>Registration</b><br><br>\r\n<b>	For Outside Participants</b><br><br>\r\n<ol><li>Register online for Robotics workshop <b><u><a href="./home.php?page=register_event">here</a></u></b>.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Take two print outs of the registration form which gets generated after you register online.<br><br></li>\r\n<li>Bring the registration form for Workshop along with you on the day of workshop along with the fee and report at the registration desk at MNNIT Allahabad.<br><br></li></ol>\r\n\r\n<b>For MNNITians</b><br><br>\r\nContact the hostel coordinators for registration.<br><br>\r\n\r\n', 'y'),
('robotics_workshop', 3, 'Contacts', '<table><tr height="40px">\r\n  <td width="400">Tushar Garg </td>\r\n<td width="400">+91-9411244393</td><td width="400">tushargarg.100@gmail.com</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="40px">\r\n  <td width="400">Abhishek Agarwal	</td>\r\n<td width="400">+91-9236871656</td><td width="400">abhiagarwal53@gmail.com</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<br><br>	', 'y'),
('code_masters', 2, 'Event Format', '<br /><br /><ol><li> Event is of 2 hours duration. \r\n \r\n<br /><br /></li><li>Event will have 5-6 problems of varying difficulty levels according to   \r\ntheir marks. \r\n \r\n<br /><br /></li><li>The questions will be of basic programming in C , C++ or Java. \r\n \r\n<br /><br /></li><li>No act of indiscipline will be tolerated. \r\n \r\n<br /><br /></li><li>Only one computer will be provided to each team. <br /><br /></li></ol>\r\n ', 'y'),
('code_masters', 3, 'Rules', ' <br /><br /><ol><li>\r\nTeam of maximum three is allowed. One person cannot be a part of   \r\nmore than one team. \r\n \r\n<br /><br /></li><li>Only two teams from each school can participate \r\n \r\n<br /><br /></li><li>Languages allowed: C/C++/Java. \r\n \r\n<br /><br /></li><li>Discussion of topics among the different teams at the time of event is \r\n  strictly prohibited. \r\n \r\n<br /><br /></li><li>Students cannot access internet either through computer or in any ways \r\n  during the event. \r\n \r\n    \r\n \r\n<br /><br /></li><li>Decision of the co-ordinators is final and co-ordinators have right to change \r\n  any of the rule if required. \r\n \r\n \r\n<br /><br /></li><li>Violation of any rule or any act of misconduct can lead to the team''s \r\n  disqualification from Jigyasa. \r\n \r\n<br /><br /></li><li>Use of any electronic gadget (mobile phones,calculators,etc.) is strictly \r\n  prohibited. <br /><br /></li></ol>\r\n ', 'y'),
('code_masters', 4, 'FAQ', '\r\n<br><br>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 1.</td><td>Who can participate?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Any student from any School in India or abroad can participate.</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 2.</td><td> What are the technical requirements for the final coding rounds? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> Simple basic programming concepts are atleast required and any \r\nof the following programming languages: <br><br>\r\nC, C++, JAVA </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 3.</td><td> What is the size of each team? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Each team can have a maximum of 3 participants. </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 4.</td><td>Where can I get more information regarding the event? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td>Send any queries regarding the event to \r\n<b><a href="mailto:jigyasa.avishkar2k11@gmail.com">jigyasa.avishkar2k11@gmail.com</a></b> with subject as "QUERY".  </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 5.</td><td> What will be schedule of the event?</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> The entire Jigyasa schedule would be posted on the website soon.</td></tr>\r\n<tr height="15"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Q 6.</td><td>Will Code Masters clash with other events of Jigyasa? </td></tr>\r\n<tr height="8"></tr>\r\n<tr valign="top"><td width="50px">Ans:</td><td> No Each event will have a different slot and a team can freely   \r\nparticipate in any other event as well. </td></tr>\r\n</table><br/><br/>', 'y'),
('hack_o_mania', 1, 'Introduction', '<br /><br /><h4 align="center">\r\nETHICAL HACKING WORKSHOP "HACK-O-MANIA" on 24th and 25th September by Techdefence</h4><br /><br />\r\n<p align="justify"><b><u>ABOUT TECHDEFENCE</u></b><br /><br />\r\nTechDefence Pvt Ltd is young but leading company basically concentrating upon the skills of young members. Technologies were formed to meet the demands of security concern of the IT industry in the web. TechDefence Consulting successfully tackle the growing number of security treats in websites through a series of test conducted by some renowned security experts which will finally end up giving a complete solution of web 2.0 along with the security. TechDefence is founded by  Sunny Vaghela  who has contributed his knowledge of Ethical Hacking, Cyber Crime Investigation & Forensics towards society since last 2 years. TechDefence has also dedicated itself to the training and development of expert professionals in order to meet the ever-growing  challenges of technology industry. Now we are calculating to launch ourselves globally seek and cross-frontiers that we have never attempted before. we are currently working into following services domain.<br><br>\r\n<b><u>Cyber Crime Investigations:</u></b><br><br>\r\nAnalyzing, investigating and accumulating the digital evidence and cyber trails is better known as Cyber Crime Investigation. It can be found in computer hard disks, cell phones, CDs, DVDs, floppies, computer networks, the Internet etc. Digital evidence and cyber trails can be derived from pictures, (stangnography), encrypted files, password protected files, deleted files, formatted hard disks, deleted emails, chat transcripts etc. Digital evidence and cyber trails are generally related to online banking frauds, online share trading fraud, source code theft, credit card fraud, tax evasion, virus attacks, cyber sabotage, phishing attacks, email hijacking, denial of service, hacking, divorce cases, murder cases, organized crime, terrorist operations, defamation, pornography, extortion, smuggling etc.<br><br> \r\n<u><b>Cyber Laws Consulting:</b></u><br><br>\r\nTechnoLegal, a branch of TechDefence, is the Cyber law Consultancy which is an online internet based nonpareil and pioneering consultancy dedicated exclusively to Cyber laws. Cyber law includes the laws relating to Cyberspace, Internet, and World Wide Web and indeed, is a blend of many legal disciplines such as intellectual property, privacy, criminal,  jurisdiction, freedom of expressions, etc. In quintessence, cyber law is an endeavor to actuate  laws conceived for the physical world to human operations on the Internet. TechnoLegal is the Consultancy that addresses all your Cyber law requirements and issues. It aspires to ensure you a veridical analysis of contemporary and evolving trends in Cyber  law according to your queries. TechnoLegal, a completely new concept of consultancy online, is one stop that takes care of all your legal exigencies in cyberspace. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b><u>Vulnerability Assessment & Penetration Testing: </u></b><br><br>\r\n Penetration Test is a method of actively evaluating the security of a computer system or a network through simulation of a controlled and managed intrusion into your system by a malicious user, known as a cracker. Active analysis of the system for any potential vulnerability that may result from  poor or improper system configuration is carried out. This analysis is carried out from the perspective of a potential attacked, and can involve active exploitation if security vulnerabilities. The results are then documented in a report which is presented  at a debriefing session, where questions can be answered and corrective strategies can be freely discussed. Penetration Testing will help you cost-effectively reduce risk, achieve and maintain regulatory compliance and reach your security goals. Vulnerability Assessment provides a clear and in-depth understanding of how vulnerable, your network, servers and applications are to attacks.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b><u>Security Audits:</u></b><br><br>\r\nSecurity Audits: A computer seurity audit is a systematic, measurable technical assessment of how the organization''s security policy is employed at a specific site. Computer security auditors work with the full knowledge of the organization, at times with considerable inside information, in order to understand the resources to be audited. Security audits do not take place in a vacuum; they are part of the on-going process of defining and maintaining effective security policies. This is not just a conference room activity. It involves everyone who uses any computer resources throughout the organization.<br><br> \r\nGiven the dynamic nature of computer configurations and information storage, some managers may wonder if there is truly any way to check the security ledgers, so to speak. Security audits provide such a tool, a fair and measurable way to examine how secure a site really is? Computer security auditors perform their work though a personal interview, vulnerability scans examination of operating system settings, analyses of network shares, and historical data. They are concerned primarily with how security policies - the foundation of any effective organizational security strategy - are actually used. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b><u>Cyber Forensics:</u></b>  <br><br>\r\nWith the right application of science and technology for acquisition, preservation, identification, analysis, and presentation of digital evidence or data in a way, we preserve the integrity of the digital information blending it with the legal acceptability. While applying the right methods that work well in the court of law, we put forward our expert witness, proficient testimony and data recovery efforts that result in the success of eventualities. Our team comprises of members that excel in the field of electronic investigation, corporate investigation and litigation support. We aim to address all cyber forensic exigencies.  TechForensics  is committed to research and development in this discipline of forensics. We provide the highest quality instructor interactive training to help legal firms, accounting firms, government and law enforcement agencies for better performance in the cyber forensic matters. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b><u>Training/workshops:</u></b><br><br>\r\nLooking at the Numbers of Cyber Crimes since last many years, We at TechDefence providem straining on Ethical hacking & Cyber Crime Investigation to students, IT professionals, law professionals, bank employees as well as police officials. The training gives participant advanced knowledge about hacking, cyber crime investigation & forensics. <br><br>\r\n', 'y'),
